It made me think of when I was a child.

257
00:15:31,250 --> 00:15:36,690
And this time Sugiyama has also
put her child out on their first errand.

258
00:15:36,680 --> 00:15:38,950
Yes, I did indeed.

259
00:15:39,810 --> 00:15:41,590
How do you feel right now?

260
00:15:41,580 --> 00:15:45,970
I feel nervous and all kinds of weird feelings are mixed in while watching this.

261
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:49,870
There are worries such as whether they can succeed or not.

262
00:15:49,860 --> 00:15:51,990
Indeed, it's very exciting to watch.

263
00:15:51,980 --> 00:15:55,660
We look forward to see your kids first errand later on.

264
00:15:55,650 --> 00:16:00,180
Sugiyama family's first errand.

265
00:16:12,380 --> 00:16:16,530
Tomiura is located in Chiba prefecture (Town of Minamibōsō).

266
00:16:16,520 --> 00:16:19,710
It's where we can find the father-daughter couple.

267
00:16:19,700 --> 00:16:23,350
The cool daughter who loves her father.

268
00:16:23,340 --> 00:16:26,500
Koiki who is 3 years and 9 months old.

269
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:26,940
So cute.

270
00:16:26,220 --> 00:16:37,290
Jinsei

271
00:16:26,930 --> 00:16:31,870
The day her little brother - Doushi - was born she turned into a big sister overnight.

272
00:16:31,860 --> 00:16:37,750
"I love my father" is what she's been saying a lot lately.

273
00:16:37,740 --> 00:16:41,830
She will go on an errand for her father.

274
00:16:41,820 --> 00:16:46,530
Those are dad's legs and his hands.

275
00:16:50,720 --> 00:16:53,450
What about a kiss?

276
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:54,820
Eh?

277
00:16:54,810 --> 00:16:57,340
Won't do it, ha!

278
00:16:57,330 --> 00:16:59,130
What are they doing?

279
00:16:59,120 --> 00:17:01,550
They have a great relationship.

280
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:02,660
Will you do it?

281
00:17:02,650 --> 00:17:06,660
As the mother told us.
The two of them are always like this.

282
00:17:06,650 --> 00:17:10,340
Rather than father and daughter
they behave like a couple.

283
00:17:10,330 --> 00:17:11,820
How nice.

284
00:17:11,810 --> 00:17:15,730
The house her father grew up in is nearby.
It's a guest house.

285
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:23,390
Every morning the grandfather gets the fresh fish and prepares them for his customers.

286
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:27,300
Mom, what can I help you with?

287
00:17:27,290 --> 00:17:29,260
What a good kid.

288
00:17:29,250 --> 00:17:31,690
I will.

289
00:17:29,250 --> 00:17:31,690
Won't you help out with this?

290
00:17:31,680 --> 00:17:36,550
The truth is that since a couple of days they've been training Koiki to help out.

291
00:17:36,540 --> 00:17:39,410
Today she will do whatever they tell her to do.

292
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:41,140
Alright. I will go now.

293
00:17:41,130 --> 00:17:45,430
Father will go with grandpa to collect the recent catches.

294
00:17:45,420 --> 00:17:47,060
- Take care.
- Off I go.

295
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:50,740
He always enjoys the bento that his wife makes for lunch.

296
00:17:50,730 --> 00:17:55,070
But this time he has forgotten it on purpose.

297
00:17:56,380 --> 00:17:57,860
Whose this?

298
00:17:57,850 --> 00:18:00,020
An onigiri bento.

299
00:18:00,010 --> 00:18:01,540
Is it dad's?

300
00:18:01,530 --> 00:18:04,220
Koiki immediately noticed it.

301
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:04,230
That was quick.

302
00:18:04,220 --> 00:18:06,550
Is he still there?

303
00:18:06,540 --> 00:18:09,270
Father, hurry. Hurry.

304
00:18:08,330 --> 00:18:09,430
Hurry out.

305
00:18:09,420 --> 00:18:11,410
Daddy.

306
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:12,690
Close call.

307
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:15,140
He barely managed to escape.

308
00:18:13,690 --> 00:18:15,110
He left.

309
00:18:15,130 --> 00:18:16,860
This will be the errand.

310
00:18:16,850 --> 00:18:20,060
He left, Koiki.
What will we do?

311
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:19,530
She's so dejected.

312
00:18:20,050 --> 00:18:24,770
I can't leave the house because of the electrician coming.

313
00:18:24,760 --> 00:18:28,490
What will they do?

314
00:18:26,340 --> 00:18:27,980
She's spinning.

315
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:30,270
Where did dad go?

316
00:18:30,260 --> 00:18:32,100
To work.

317
00:18:33,280 --> 00:18:36,530
She knows that he left for the harbor.

318
00:18:37,260 --> 00:18:42,780
Grandfathers boat is waiting 2 km away from their house.

319
00:18:42,770 --> 00:18:47,150
It returns here for lunch.

320
00:18:47,140 --> 00:18:49,110
Can I ask you for help?

321
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:52,870
For my first errand?

322
00:18:52,860 --> 00:18:55,130
Did she figure out it's for the show?

323
00:18:55,720 --> 00:18:57,730
No no no, that's not it.

324
00:18:57,720 --> 00:18:58,820
Can you go?

325
00:18:58,810 --> 00:19:07,490
Last month everyone in the neighborhood was praising her big brother saying: "Wow, you were able to go on your first errand".

326
00:19:07,960 --> 00:19:14,470
Next up, I (Koiki) will go.
It's a true "first errand" fad.

327
00:19:14,940 --> 00:19:20,810
But there's one puzzling thing
in regards to Koiki's first errand.

328
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:26,290
Her mother has given her a good luck charm with words of love.

329
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:32,190
Pipi? (sounds of weeping)
It's because Koiki tends to cry very easily.

330
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:43,110
As soon as things don't go her way she will start weeping.

331
00:19:43,100 --> 00:19:48,110
That's why her dad and her made their own word.

332
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:51,750
Koiki, pipi.

333
00:19:52,810 --> 00:19:54,870
I will not cry.

334
00:19:54,860 --> 00:19:56,050
Are you a baby?

335
00:19:56,040 --> 00:19:57,550
I'm not.

336
00:19:57,540 --> 00:20:00,380
I won't cry.

337
00:19:57,540 --> 00:20:00,380
Pipi.

338
00:20:00,370 --> 00:20:02,650
She doesn't want to be called a baby.

339
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:05,100
She wants to be seen as a big sister.

340
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:09,010
Yes.

341
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:09,010
You're a big sister.

342
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:23,330
What does it say here?
It's the word we use every time you cry.

343
00:20:23,320 --> 00:20:26,580
Pipi, I will not cry.

344
00:20:26,570 --> 00:20:29,980
If you cry just look at this good luck charm, okay?

345
00:20:29,970 --> 00:20:34,190
Just look at this and give it all you got. Can you do it?

346
00:20:34,180 --> 00:20:37,970
All right, stand up. I will put it on you.

347
00:20:37,960 --> 00:20:40,850
She will be fine if she's got this charm.

348
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:42,410
Can you do it?

349
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:44,300
I wonder...

350
00:20:45,180 --> 00:20:48,020
Aiming for the coast

351
00:20:48,010 --> 00:20:52,550
her father will return to the harbor around noon for lunch.

352
00:20:53,820 --> 00:20:56,510
I'm off.

353
00:20:53,820 --> 00:20:56,510
Take care.

354
00:20:57,290 --> 00:21:00,200
I'm off.

355
00:20:57,290 --> 00:21:00,200
Take care.

356
00:21:01,250 --> 00:21:05,190
Today she departed the house without crying all pipi-like.

357
00:21:05,930 --> 00:21:06,910
How remarkable.

358
00:21:08,490 --> 00:21:11,390
Just as she promised her dad who she loves

359
00:21:11,380 --> 00:21:13,010
I won't cry anymore.

360
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:20,860
Song lyrics: She has started walking with a charm in her chest that her mother put on her...

361
00:21:20,930 --> 00:21:24,810
She uses all her strength to head for the harbor.

362
00:21:25,740 --> 00:21:27,010
She's so strong.

363
00:21:29,500 --> 00:21:32,980
- You are so cute.
- Hello there.

364
00:21:32,980 --> 00:21:36,580
There's no time for the abundance of greetings.

365
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:43,230
Even though it's a street without a crossing

366
00:21:43,220 --> 00:21:47,190
since she's a big sister she knows how to properly cross a street.

367
00:21:45,730 --> 00:21:47,190
How great.

368
00:21:51,970 --> 00:21:55,620
It's almost lunch. I wonder if the boat is about to return.

369
00:21:57,440 --> 00:21:59,870
Yes, it's over there.

370
00:22:01,010 --> 00:22:04,870
The boat is returning to the harbor.

371
00:22:03,490 --> 00:22:04,980
Thankfully.

372
00:22:04,300 --> 00:22:09,920
Original song:
By Keiko Utoku · Shingo Maekawa
The loving words from the jet of a voice

373
00:22:06,970 --> 00:22:13,380
They've already caught lots of shellfish and have returned to the harbor to deliver them.

374
00:22:16,460 --> 00:22:20,850
I wonder if they can hear her
if she shouts in a loud voice.

375
00:22:27,840 --> 00:22:29,300
A sigh instead.

376
00:22:29,290 --> 00:22:31,460
I wonder if they will come back.

377
00:22:31,450 --> 00:22:34,110
What? She will not shout for them?

378
00:22:34,100 --> 00:22:36,210
What's wrong?

379
00:22:37,040 --> 00:22:38,890
Daddy.

380
00:22:38,880 --> 00:22:46,140
Since her father is completely focused on getting the seashells out he has not noticed the Koiki is there.

381
00:22:45,250 --> 00:22:46,540
I see.

382
00:22:49,300 --> 00:22:55,220
No matter how long she's been standing there she's not shouting out to her dad.

383
00:22:56,120 --> 00:22:59,420
Oh no, is she leaving?

384
00:22:59,560 --> 00:23:01,690
Who are those people out there?

385
00:23:01,680 --> 00:23:03,550
Dad and grandpa.

386
00:23:03,540 --> 00:23:06,990
The cameraman couldn't help himself and spoke to her.

387
00:23:07,180 --> 00:23:10,290
If you shout to them don't you think they will hear you?

388
00:23:10,280 --> 00:23:12,710
She's careful since it's a first.

389
00:23:12,700 --> 00:23:16,820
And she often says "can't do it" and then gives up.

390
00:23:16,810 --> 00:23:19,700
I wonder how it will be today.

391
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:24,180
Must be a bit embarrassing for her.

392
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:26,620
Indeed. Indeed.

393
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:30,470
Nothing came out.

394
00:23:31,240 --> 00:23:37,060
Daddy. Grandpa.

395
00:23:32,620 --> 00:23:34,350
There it is.

396
00:23:37,050 --> 00:23:39,900
Daddy. Grandpa.

397
00:23:39,890 --> 00:23:44,940
Yes, she shouted out to them.
But they can't hear her.

398
00:23:44,930 --> 00:23:51,330
Her voice didn't reach them but she won't quit.

399
00:23:51,320 --> 00:23:56,650
One, two and... Father.

400
00:23:56,640 --> 00:23:59,300
Grandpa.

401
00:23:59,290 --> 00:24:06,410
At 3 years and 9 months
this is the loudest she has ever been in her life.

402
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:08,470
Koiki.

403
00:24:08,460 --> 00:24:11,770
Her voice reached her father.

404
00:24:11,760 --> 00:24:14,630
Koiki.

405
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:24,510
Daddy.

406
00:24:26,080 --> 00:24:28,300
Koiki.

407
00:24:28,920 --> 00:24:31,810
They are like lovers.

408
00:24:30,730 --> 00:24:33,870
The affectionate bond between Koiki and her dad.

409
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:42,830
You forgot your lunch.

410
00:24:44,490 --> 00:24:48,070
I came here to bring it to you.

411
00:24:48,060 --> 00:24:53,850
The voices of the two is flying across the harbor.

412
00:24:54,540 --> 00:24:59,140
O-Onigiri. You forgot it.

413
00:24:59,130 --> 00:25:01,090
Koiki.

414
00:25:01,080 --> 00:25:03,940
Daddy.

415
00:25:03,060 --> 00:25:04,340
Daddy.

416
00:25:04,330 --> 00:25:07,630
Koiki.. the harbor...

417
00:25:05,370 --> 00:25:07,270
What?

418
00:25:07,650 --> 00:25:09,850
Please wait at the harbor.

419
00:25:10,090 --> 00:25:13,110
Understood.

420
00:25:15,880 --> 00:25:18,300
Oh no, tears are starting.

421
00:25:17,880 --> 00:25:20,090
I get it. Of course they would.

422
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:28,610
Because of how long they spent touchingly shouting at each other she had to wait an extra 12 minutes for them.

423
00:25:30,980 --> 00:25:34,970
- Did you come by yourself? How great.

424
00:25:30,980 --> 00:25:34,970
- Yup.

425
00:25:34,960 --> 00:25:37,310
I came alone.

426
00:25:39,890 --> 00:25:44,620
There's also grandpas lunch.

427
00:25:39,890 --> 00:25:44,620
You also brought mine? Thank you.

428
00:25:44,610 --> 00:25:47,740
Sorry for making you wait grandpa.

429
00:25:48,410 --> 00:25:54,660
Remembering the word pipi she didn't cry even once.

430
00:25:54,650 --> 00:25:59,550
Dad, I love you.

431
00:26:01,210 --> 00:26:03,820
I also love you very much.

432
00:26:05,700 --> 00:26:08,460
There's no room for grandpa in this equation.

433
00:26:09,490 --> 00:26:11,610
- Hey grandpa.
- He looks so lonely.

434
00:26:11,600 --> 00:26:17,870
Because she excelled at this errand the father has thought up the next one.

435
00:26:17,860 --> 00:26:23,700
The filefish and turban shell that we just caught

436
00:26:23,690 --> 00:26:26,260
can you bring them to Genbei?

437
00:26:26,250 --> 00:26:28,410
Koiki responds immediately.

438
00:26:28,400 --> 00:26:35,820
She will have to bring them to the guesthouse at her fathers childhood home called Genbei.

439
00:26:36,600 --> 00:26:38,490
It's true.

440
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:40,090
See? They are right here.

441
00:26:40,080 --> 00:26:43,770
The filefish that they caught this morning are still alive.

442
00:26:43,760 --> 00:26:46,370
Koiki look.

443
00:26:46,360 --> 00:26:48,110
Looks heavy.

444
00:26:48,100 --> 00:26:49,770
Even turban shell.

445
00:26:49,760 --> 00:26:53,050
It's peeking out.

446
00:26:53,040 --> 00:26:56,540
They caught 3 of each type.

447
00:26:56,530 --> 00:26:59,590
That's quite a heavy load.
I wonder if it will be fine.

448
00:26:57,930 --> 00:27:00,270
- That's heavy.
- Yeah, it will be.

449
00:27:01,450 --> 00:27:05,150
First she will go to the marketplace
and get them to add ice.

450
00:27:05,140 --> 00:27:10,710
The guesthouse Genbei is further away.

451
00:27:10,700 --> 00:27:11,150
What?

452
00:27:11,650 --> 00:27:13,630
Koiki will you use this one?

453
00:27:11,650 --> 00:27:13,630
Yeah.

454
00:27:13,620 --> 00:27:16,700
A secret weapon.

455
00:27:16,690 --> 00:27:18,810
What is a secret weapon?

456
00:27:19,060 --> 00:27:22,820
Father got it from a hardware store just this morning.

457
00:27:22,810 --> 00:27:29,620
For 2950 yen.
With this she can carry anything.

458
00:27:29,610 --> 00:27:30,890
I'm begging you.

459
00:27:29,610 --> 00:27:30,890
I'm heading off.

460
00:27:30,880 --> 00:27:34,970
The father has been planning for this day for a month.

461
00:27:34,960 --> 00:27:36,850
Do your best until you reach Genbei.

462
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:40,170
Just hoping that this will be a good memory for Koiki.

463
00:27:40,210 --> 00:27:43,450
You two love each other a lot.

464
00:27:43,860 --> 00:27:45,870
I still hold back on my emotions.

465
00:27:46,810 --> 00:27:47,860
Father.

466
00:27:47,850 --> 00:27:51,270
And about the expression of love that cost 2950 yen.

467
00:27:51,860 --> 00:27:55,070
Koiki has taken it to her.

468
00:27:55,060 --> 00:27:59,490
Since it is past noon calm has fallen over the marketplace.

469
00:27:59,480 --> 00:28:06,130
Her fathers senior at his middle school -
Masayoshi - works there.

470
00:28:06,120 --> 00:28:11,620
They've arranged that if she shouts
"Masayoshi" then he will come out.

471
00:28:11,610 --> 00:28:16,610
But she's a bit scared by her fathers senior.

472
00:28:17,580 --> 00:28:19,750
Even though he's a kind person.

473
00:28:18,620 --> 00:28:20,470
Too scary looking.

474
00:28:19,740 --> 00:28:24,310
It might be due to him always talking in a loud voice.

475
00:28:24,300 --> 00:28:27,230
Wonder if Koiki will be alright.

476
00:28:28,370 --> 00:28:34,540
Let's see if she will manage to
call him in a confident voice.

477
00:28:38,530 --> 00:28:40,100
Masayoshi.

478
00:28:40,090 --> 00:28:41,500
She did.

479
00:28:41,490 --> 00:28:43,230
I came on an errand by myself.

480
00:28:43,220 --> 00:28:45,860
An errand? To do what?

481
00:28:45,850 --> 00:28:49,950
Did you come by yourself?
How remarkable you are.

482
00:28:49,940 --> 00:28:52,060
What? He's a very kind person.

483
00:28:52,050 --> 00:28:55,570
Just like her father. Men of the sea
are both strong and kind.

484
00:28:55,560 --> 00:28:58,830
Masayoshi has worked at the fish market for 26 years.

485
00:28:58,820 --> 00:29:03,470
He's working there as a general worker.

486
00:29:03,460 --> 00:29:04,810
There's some tape inside.

487
00:29:04,800 --> 00:29:08,590
Oh, so they prepared some tape for it.
What will you do with it?

488
00:29:08,580 --> 00:29:10,350
This?

489
00:29:10,340 --> 00:29:11,550
To put some ice in it.

490
00:29:11,540 --> 00:29:14,970
Put ice in it. Alright, I will put some in for you.

491
00:29:14,960 --> 00:29:18,810
Since it's after hours for the market
he's been waiting all this time.

492
00:29:18,800 --> 00:29:19,910
Thank you.

493
00:29:19,900 --> 00:29:21,930
This will be enough, right?

494
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:23,250
Be careful.

495
00:29:23,240 --> 00:29:25,810
He's known her since she was born.

496
00:29:25,800 --> 00:29:27,210
He's so kind.

497
00:29:35,210 --> 00:29:40,340
From just being thought of as a baby
she is now regarded as a big sister.

498
00:29:40,330 --> 00:29:45,830
Thanks to daddy's secret weapon carrying it would be easy-peasy is what they thought but...

499
00:29:45,820 --> 00:29:49,060
it's not that easy either.

500
00:29:49,050 --> 00:29:54,350
Koiki who usually quits right away won't quit today.

501
00:29:54,340 --> 00:29:58,210
She pulls with all her power.

502
00:29:58,200 --> 00:30:01,510
She could've just used the road.

503
00:30:01,500 --> 00:30:05,130
Thanks to pipi she won't cry or give up

504
00:30:05,120 --> 00:30:09,620
cause she is carrying her fathers catch of the day.

505
00:30:10,210 --> 00:30:14,330
She has arrived at the guesthouse Genbei.
The house her father grew up in.

506
00:30:14,320 --> 00:30:20,940
Her dad told her that when she's at the entrance she should yell out: "Mom, please come and help."

507
00:30:20,930 --> 00:30:22,430
Ah, did she arrive?

508
00:30:22,420 --> 00:30:26,810
She noticed her but she has decided not to come out until she is being called.

509
00:30:26,800 --> 00:30:30,690
She's not calling for her mom.

510
00:30:30,680 --> 00:30:32,610
Is she carrying it alone?

511
00:30:31,720 --> 00:30:34,780
She intends to bring it in all by herself.

512
00:30:34,770 --> 00:30:36,780
That's quite impressive.

513
00:30:37,240 --> 00:30:43,350
She has made sure to open the doors wide open
but it's still heavy from all the ice.

514
00:30:47,180 --> 00:30:53,490
She can't get it over the last 10 cm of the last step.

515
00:30:55,890 --> 00:30:58,750
Even though she could've gotten her mother to help.

516
00:30:59,930 --> 00:31:01,180
She's great.

