00:55:53,530 --> 00:55:58,660
She has seen the front of the building this time.
I wonder if she will be fine.

1046
00:55:58,650 --> 00:56:01,140
She's looking at the pamphlet and comparing it.

1047
00:56:01,130 --> 00:56:04,070
The Japanese confectionary shop.

1048
00:56:04,060 --> 00:56:06,710
The shop is here if she turns.

1049
00:56:06,700 --> 00:56:10,970
However she went straight.

1050
00:56:10,960 --> 00:56:13,470
- Made to run.
- The adults are.

1051
00:56:13,460 --> 00:56:16,700
Rather than shooting they are running more.

1052
00:56:16,690 --> 00:56:17,780
So fast.

1053
00:56:17,200 --> 00:56:19,660
They must also be heading for that famous shop.

1054
00:56:19,650 --> 00:56:21,060
They can't keep up.

1055
00:56:21,200 --> 00:56:23,760
Cream puffs. Cream puffs. Cream puffs.

1056
00:56:23,750 --> 00:56:25,910
She's been out for less than 10 minutes.

1057
00:56:26,460 --> 00:56:31,700
"She's already back" the shop owner must be wondering.

1058
00:56:41,670 --> 00:56:43,330
Cream puffs please.

1059
00:56:43,320 --> 00:56:47,130
They haven't baked yet.

1060
00:56:47,120 --> 00:56:48,410
I see.

1061
00:56:48,400 --> 00:56:51,540
It will take a bit longer. Please come again.

1062
00:56:51,530 --> 00:56:53,910
I will be back later.

1063
00:56:53,900 --> 00:56:57,320
Despite having seen the picture of the correct shop.

1064
00:56:57,310 --> 00:57:01,090
She didn't notice that this is a different shop?

1065
00:56:59,840 --> 00:57:01,400
She runs so much.

1066
00:57:01,080 --> 00:57:03,520
She's going back to her fathers place.

1067
00:57:03,510 --> 00:57:06,480
And the staff is trying to reach the office first.

1068
00:57:06,910 --> 00:57:08,360
How rough.

1069
00:57:08,920 --> 00:57:10,640
She went straight ahead?

1070
00:57:10,630 --> 00:57:12,980
Better visit the shrine.

1071
00:57:10,630 --> 00:57:12,980
The shrine?

1072
00:57:12,970 --> 00:57:16,790
Everyone is competing against An.

1073
00:57:15,350 --> 00:57:17,860
So many are coming out.

1074
00:57:17,850 --> 00:57:19,860
The shrine.

1075
00:57:19,850 --> 00:57:21,790
Why all of a sudden.

1076
00:57:23,550 --> 00:57:28,100
When out for walks with her mother she always visits this shrine.

1077
00:57:28,090 --> 00:57:32,200
These rocks are called Shimeishi and can be found in the ocean.

1078
00:57:32,190 --> 00:57:35,500
They've been here since over 100 years ago.

1079
00:57:37,480 --> 00:57:40,010
Jingle jangle, she's rich.

1080
00:57:40,000 --> 00:57:42,450
How many yen will she put out?

1081
00:57:42,440 --> 00:57:44,340
She's not putting anything in?

1082
00:57:44,330 --> 00:57:46,230
I have no clue.

1083
00:57:46,790 --> 00:57:48,270
A shame.

1084
00:57:47,820 --> 00:57:49,810
She's already leaving?

1085
00:57:49,800 --> 00:57:52,340
She didn't even make a wish.

1086
00:57:52,330 --> 00:57:57,590
The cameramen have no clue anymore.
They are being made to follow her whims.

1087
00:57:57,580 --> 00:58:04,020
An is giving the fight of her life.
But what she intends to do is hard to decipher.

1088
00:58:02,380 --> 00:58:04,000
She's so busy.

1089
00:58:04,010 --> 00:58:05,720
They are still making them.

1090
00:58:05,710 --> 00:58:11,020
They are still making them?
What did the old guy say?

1091
00:58:11,010 --> 00:58:12,930
What? It was an old woman.

1092
00:58:12,920 --> 00:58:15,190
Old woman? And she's making them now?

1093
00:58:15,180 --> 00:58:17,940
Wait, was there ever a woman running that shop?

1094
00:58:17,930 --> 00:58:20,770
Which shop did you go to?

1095
00:58:20,760 --> 00:58:21,850
He noticed it.

1096
00:58:21,840 --> 00:58:27,480
Did you go to the wrong shop?
The shop is this way.

1097
00:58:27,470 --> 00:58:29,300
Go towards the shrine.

1098
00:58:29,290 --> 00:58:36,490
There are many narrow streets here but if she goes this way it will be easy to find.

1099
00:58:37,100 --> 00:58:38,020
Just go this way.

1100
00:58:38,010 --> 00:58:41,450
That's right. It's easier to spot from this direction.

1101
00:58:41,320 --> 00:58:42,630
I will go this way.

1102
00:58:42,330 --> 00:58:43,210
Why why?

1103
00:58:44,140 --> 00:58:45,560
Why this way?

1104
00:58:44,910 --> 00:58:46,340
Her conviction is strong.

1105
00:58:45,540 --> 00:58:50,020
She's inherited this from her dad that she refuses to bow down from her opinions.

1106
00:58:50,190 --> 00:58:52,200
What color coin should I use?

1107
00:58:52,190 --> 00:58:53,210
She came back.

1108
00:58:53,200 --> 00:58:54,450
The brown coins.

1109
00:58:54,440 --> 00:58:57,240
She didn't know the kind of money to put in the box.

1110
00:58:57,230 --> 00:58:59,000
So that's what it was.

1111
00:58:58,080 --> 00:58:59,630
I will be back.

1112
00:58:59,620 --> 00:59:02,040
I see. The shrine is that way.

1113
00:59:02,030 --> 00:59:04,730
[Sponsor announcement]

1114
00:59:21,400 --> 00:59:25,930
I wish my mother will not be sick.

1115
00:59:25,920 --> 00:59:28,470
The mother said she had a sore throat.

1116
00:59:28,720 --> 00:59:32,260
Rather than the cream puffs
the most important thing is mother.

1117
00:59:32,250 --> 00:59:34,390
Ah, it was over here.

1118
00:59:34,380 --> 00:59:35,780
I forgot.

1119
00:59:35,770 --> 00:59:38,680
Cream puffs. Cream puffs.

1120
00:59:38,670 --> 00:59:41,850
The shop is just outside of the gates.

1121
00:59:41,840 --> 00:59:44,420
Why is she going to the side?

1122
00:59:46,060 --> 00:59:47,210
I'm sweating.

1123
00:59:47,200 --> 00:59:49,080
From all the running.

1124
00:59:49,070 --> 00:59:52,100
She taking a small break.

1125
00:59:52,140 --> 00:59:55,170
She's just taking the blouse off.

1126
00:59:55,160 --> 00:59:57,940
She's confirming that she didn't forget anything.

1127
00:59:57,780 --> 00:59:59,000
Admirable.

1128
00:59:58,350 --> 01:00:01,000
She should see the shop just up the road.

1129
01:00:01,050 --> 01:00:04,010
The cameraman has gone in first.

1130
01:00:04,000 --> 01:00:07,390
Look behind you. Behind you.

1131
01:00:08,720 --> 01:00:09,710
Dunno.

1132
01:00:10,120 --> 01:00:14,180
She went back even though it's right there.

1133
01:00:14,170 --> 01:00:16,250
Why can't she spot it?

1134
01:00:16,640 --> 01:00:17,960
Ah, An?

1135
01:00:19,240 --> 01:00:20,470
Did you purchase it?

1136
01:00:20,460 --> 01:00:21,970
Great that you came back.

1137
01:00:21,960 --> 01:00:25,220
She didn't mention the shrine.

1138
01:00:25,560 --> 01:00:27,240
Did you not spot it?

1139
01:00:25,560 --> 01:00:27,240
No.

1140
01:00:27,230 --> 01:00:28,760
It wasn't there?

1141
01:00:27,230 --> 01:00:28,760
Yep.

1142
01:00:28,750 --> 01:00:36,530
An, perhaps you didn't see the picture.
The front looks like this. The sign has green and red letters.

1143
01:00:36,520 --> 01:00:38,840
I'm supposed to look at this?

1144
01:00:38,830 --> 01:00:44,690
An was looking at the cream puff picture.
She wasn't looking at the facade.

1145
01:00:44,680 --> 01:00:47,430
Off you go. This way.

1146
01:00:47,420 --> 01:00:51,650
Around the corner here. Take care and thanks.

1147
01:00:51,640 --> 01:00:54,390
This is the 4th trip.

1148
01:00:54,380 --> 01:00:58,980
This time she is looking at the shop facade.

1149
01:00:58,970 --> 01:01:01,060
Can she find it?

1150
01:01:01,070 --> 01:01:05,480
It's right there. The green and red letters on the sign.

1151
01:01:08,280 --> 01:01:09,960
Ah, found it.

1152
01:01:09,950 --> 01:01:11,620
Thankfully.

1153
01:01:12,400 --> 01:01:16,850
Right, left. All clear, I can continue.

1154
01:01:16,800 --> 01:01:17,860
Nice.

1155
01:01:17,850 --> 01:01:22,570
She's doing it properly.
But she's also hurrying.

1156
01:01:22,560 --> 01:01:27,140
She was asked to purchase two.

1157
01:01:28,140 --> 01:01:29,670
Welcome.

1158
01:01:29,890 --> 01:01:32,810
One cream puff two of those.

1159
01:01:32,800 --> 01:01:34,620
Two? Okay.

1160
01:01:34,990 --> 01:01:39,300
He has them. These are those made with wasanbon sugar.

1161
01:01:39,290 --> 01:01:44,890
One is 175 yen. She put out a 1000 bill so now her purse will jangle even more.

1162
01:01:44,880 --> 01:01:48,500
She became even richer.

1163
01:01:48,490 --> 01:01:50,330
Do you know the way back?

1164
01:01:48,490 --> 01:01:50,330
Yes.

1165
01:01:50,360 --> 01:01:52,690
Please don't get lost again.

1166
01:01:52,680 --> 01:01:55,390
Please wait a bit.

1167
01:01:54,280 --> 01:01:55,170
Phew.

1168
01:01:55,380 --> 01:01:56,550
A reward.

1169
01:01:56,540 --> 01:01:57,520
It's a cookie.

1170
01:01:57,510 --> 01:01:58,780
Enjoy it.

1171
01:01:58,770 --> 01:02:00,620
She received a reward.

1172
01:02:00,610 --> 01:02:03,690
Thank you.

1173
01:02:00,610 --> 01:02:04,250
You're welcome. Take care on your way back.

1174
01:02:04,270 --> 01:02:05,950
After saying her thanks.

1175
01:02:05,940 --> 01:02:09,300
Right, left. All clear, I can continue.

1176
01:02:09,290 --> 01:02:10,650
Being safe in traffic.

1177
01:02:10,640 --> 01:02:12,060
Bye bye.

1178
01:02:12,050 --> 01:02:14,690
She can finally return.

1179
01:02:14,680 --> 01:02:16,410
I will give it to dad.

1180
01:02:16,400 --> 01:02:17,880
Cream puffs.

1181
01:02:18,060 --> 01:02:20,280
Yep.

1182
01:02:18,060 --> 01:02:20,280
You managed to buy it?

1183
01:02:20,270 --> 01:02:21,790
Amazing.

1184
01:02:21,780 --> 01:02:24,200
I found it by myself.

1185
01:02:24,190 --> 01:02:25,320
Perfect.

1186
01:02:26,920 --> 01:02:29,030
Let's take some pictures.

1187
01:02:29,360 --> 01:02:30,850
Here I go.

1188
01:02:30,840 --> 01:02:34,890
She's properly assisting with the reflector board.

1189
01:02:34,880 --> 01:02:38,680
The dad looks cool as he is focused on taking the pictures.

1190
01:02:38,670 --> 01:02:39,930
See?

1191
01:02:39,920 --> 01:02:41,800
Thank you.

1192
01:02:45,380 --> 01:02:47,040
You can eat this one.

1193
01:02:47,030 --> 01:02:49,920
That's why she likes photoshoots of food.

1194
01:02:51,690 --> 01:02:52,770
Delicious.

1195
01:02:52,760 --> 01:02:57,830
Ah, she forgot. She ordered cream puffs at this shop.

1196
01:03:03,180 --> 01:03:04,770
And the dad doesn't know.

1197
01:03:04,760 --> 01:03:07,680
He only knew about the shop over there.

1198
01:03:04,760 --> 01:03:07,680
That's right. That's right.

1199
01:03:07,670 --> 01:03:12,060
He really made her walk around.

1200
01:03:07,670 --> 01:03:12,060
There was a proper reason to get those.

1201
01:03:12,050 --> 01:03:14,650
Why did you come to the shrine?

1202
01:03:14,640 --> 01:03:17,190
I saw you were crying a bit during the conundrum.

1203
01:03:17,180 --> 01:03:19,190
I couldn't stand it.

1204
01:03:19,180 --> 01:03:25,930
I was touched when she properly asked
for her mothers good health.

1205
01:03:25,920 --> 01:03:27,280
Very touching.

1206
01:03:27,270 --> 01:03:30,060
Makes me curious about the cream puffs she ordered.

1207
01:03:27,610 --> 01:03:33,370
On the way back from the errand.

1208
01:03:30,050 --> 01:03:32,680
I wonder until how late the old lady waited for her.

1209
01:03:32,670 --> 01:03:39,850
As a gift for her mother that had a sore throat
they apparently collected it on the way home.

1210
01:03:38,440 --> 01:03:39,720
That's great.

1211
01:03:39,930 --> 01:03:43,020
The bus will be here in a bit.

1212
01:03:43,010 --> 01:03:48,300
These brothers will ride a bus to complete their errand.

1213
01:03:48,290 --> 01:03:49,990
He's so small.

1214
01:03:49,660 --> 01:03:56,040
The 4 year and 3 months old brother and his little brother
at 2 years and 4 months who keeps asking if it's coming.

1215
01:03:49,920 --> 01:03:54,040
Shuya

1216
01:03:51,960 --> 01:03:54,040
Kanaya

1217
01:03:56,030 --> 01:04:04,470
The one who planned this errand and let his little brother join is their mother.

1218
01:04:00,460 --> 01:04:01,730
She's standing there.

1219
01:04:04,460 --> 01:04:07,590
As their mother I am confident that they can handle it.

1220
01:04:07,580 --> 01:04:12,870
Some strong words.
She has a special memory associated with them.

1221
01:04:12,860 --> 01:04:20,160
The city of Ikeda in Tokushima prefecture where the dad who loves mountains was brought up.

1222
01:04:20,150 --> 01:04:25,620
The dad purchased a house with a nice view.

1223
01:04:25,610 --> 01:04:27,990
The wall is full of family pictures.

1224
01:04:27,980 --> 01:04:32,210
When the kids were smaller or that time they visited Okinawa.

1225
01:04:32,200 --> 01:04:37,640
In the four years of their marriage the wall has already filled up.

1226
01:04:37,630 --> 01:04:42,400
But the dad is no longer with us.

1227
01:04:42,390 --> 01:04:45,020
He died 2 years ago.

1228
01:04:46,100 --> 01:04:51,780
He left for his lumberjack job as usual on that day.

1229
01:04:51,420 --> 01:04:56,410
Location of the accident

1230
01:04:51,770 --> 01:04:55,610
But a tree suddenly fell on him.

1231
01:04:57,470 --> 01:05:06,820
When papa died I cried so much.
The two of us did. Every evening.

1232
01:05:06,810 --> 01:05:15,210
It was just after the little brother was born. The one who was always by his mothers side was the 2 year old brother.

1233
01:05:15,200 --> 01:05:21,460
It hit me like a switch. I don't remember when.
Suddenly I just decided not to cry anymore.

1234
01:05:21,450 --> 01:05:26,930
I won't cry anymore. Won't cry
in front of the kids anymore. Not again.

1235
01:05:26,920 --> 01:05:34,390
But on that day I decided that while there are dads and mothers I need to fulfill both of those roles.

1236
01:05:34,680 --> 01:05:40,740
The big brother behaves properly after having watched his mother from the sidelines.

1237
01:05:40,730 --> 01:05:47,030
When the little brother becomes unmanageable the one to take the reins is the big brother.

1238
01:05:47,020 --> 01:05:52,770
It's like he has taken the responsibility of his father.

1239
01:05:52,760 --> 01:05:56,400
I rely on the big brother.

1240
01:05:57,870 --> 01:06:02,090
The big brother loves to make his mother happy.

1241
01:06:02,960 --> 01:06:08,410
His father loved tulips.
Just as he loved nature.

1242
01:06:08,400 --> 01:06:12,710
So for the errand they've decided to get some flowers for him.

1243
01:06:12,700 --> 01:06:16,490
Kanaya at 2 years and four months still doesn't talk.

1244
01:06:16,480 --> 01:06:20,560
But he's fine with his brother on his side.

1245
01:06:20,550 --> 01:06:22,210
He depends on him.

1246
01:06:22,200 --> 01:06:24,860
The bus which is running late finally came.

1247
01:06:24,850 --> 01:06:26,050
It came.

1248
01:06:27,260 --> 01:06:29,010
Stop, please stop.

1249
01:06:29,000 --> 01:06:30,900
He noticed the brothers hands.

1250
01:06:29,840 --> 01:06:31,560
What a relief.

1251
01:06:31,950 --> 01:06:38,720
What a relief. This bus comes once every 2 hours.

1252
01:06:38,710 --> 01:06:40,380
They rode it.

1253
01:06:40,370 --> 01:06:44,770
They rode it. It's hard to see because of the tinted windows.

1254
01:06:44,760 --> 01:06:47,540
The windows on the bus are tinted.

1255
01:06:47,530 --> 01:06:53,110
The cameraman rehearsed this shot with the bus that passed 2 hours earlier and has waited since then.

1256
01:06:53,100 --> 01:06:57,270
Eh? With this type of windows we can't look inside.

1257
01:06:55,920 --> 01:06:57,690
Can't see a thing.

1258
01:06:57,680 --> 01:06:59,810
The cameraman on the bus.

1259
01:06:59,800 --> 01:07:05,760
Big brother looks serious.
And with his bright red cheeks.

1260
01:07:05,940 --> 01:07:08,670
What about the youngest of them?

1261
01:07:09,340 --> 01:07:15,670
Getting sleepy from the ride but he has nothing to worry about. Since his brother is by his side.

1262
01:07:17,270 --> 01:07:20,910
Protect him, big brother.

1263
01:07:22,460 --> 01:07:23,590
He's falling asleep.

1264
01:07:24,430 --> 01:07:30,070
The bus has arrived at the terminal.
This is also where they should catch it on the way back.

1265
01:07:30,060 --> 01:07:32,490
He's fast asleep.

1266
01:07:32,480 --> 01:07:39,620
We are getting off, Kanaya. You can't sleep here.

1267
01:07:39,610 --> 01:07:45,430
They've received the bus fare separately.
Oh no, this is for the flowers.

1268
01:07:45,420 --> 01:07:47,860
Oh no, he took out the 1000 yen bill.

1269
01:07:47,850 --> 01:07:50,850
Now the purse is full of spare change.

1270
01:07:52,970 --> 01:07:55,270
Let's walk to the flower shop.

1271
01:07:55,260 --> 01:07:58,700
Yes, they have to walk to the flower shop.

1272
01:07:58,690 --> 01:08:03,570
The road is straight forward.
They always come by car here with their mother.

1273
01:08:03,560 --> 01:08:07,160
They might not notice when going by car
but the street is on a slope.

1274
01:08:07,150 --> 01:08:10,990
Which they have to ascend on the way back.

1275
01:08:10,980 --> 01:08:16,040
Furthermore it takes about 2 hours to go there and back.
There's no time to roam around.

1276
01:08:14,780 --> 01:08:16,040
Better hurry.

1277
01:08:16,030 --> 01:08:20,870
They have to walk in line
since the pavement is narrow.

1278
01:08:20,860 --> 01:08:23,470
He's properly following his big brother.

1279
01:08:23,460 --> 01:08:27,580
Kanaya doesn't speak but he's good on his feet.

1280
01:08:27,850 --> 01:08:29,000
Hole.

1281
01:08:28,990 --> 01:08:29,930
Hole?

1282
01:08:30,390 --> 01:08:34,520
They are taught to walk in the line
where the holes are by their mother.

1283
01:08:34,510 --> 01:08:38,660
His brother is checking if Kanaya is walking properly.

1284
01:08:40,060 --> 01:08:44,230
After the check they can continue.

1285
01:08:41,800 --> 01:08:44,230
Pushed him.

1286
01:08:44,670 --> 01:08:55,330
But their speeds are completely different.
Little brother who can't speak a word wants to call out "wait".

1287
01:08:55,320 --> 01:08:58,010
Brobro.

1288
01:08:58,000 --> 01:09:03,640
You've become capable of saying "brobro", Kanaya?

1289
01:09:04,510 --> 01:09:09,000
His first words and they were "brobro".

1290
01:09:08,990 --> 01:09:11,480
A rapid development on this errand.

1291
01:09:11,470 --> 01:09:17,020
When you follow your brother with all your might you grow strong.

1292
01:09:18,230 --> 01:09:19,330
Hand.

1293
01:09:19,320 --> 01:09:20,680
Hand hand.

1294
01:09:20,670 --> 01:09:22,550
He even said "hands".

1295
01:09:23,020 --> 01:09:26,200
Even at home there are times
when he doesn't want to hold hands.

1296
01:09:26,190 --> 01:09:30,840
But today is an errand and his brother is his new father-figure.

1297
01:09:30,830 --> 01:09:33,030
Ah, it's over there.

1298
01:09:33,020 --> 01:09:35,510
They can see the flower shop.

1299
01:09:37,010 --> 01:09:42,070
Their father would often stop by
to purchase flowers for his wife.

1300
01:09:42,060 --> 01:09:46,360
He would get the flowers of the season every week.

1301
01:09:46,350 --> 01:09:52,150
Their father who worked in the mountain-side especially prefered bigleaf hydrangea.

1302
01:09:52,140 --> 01:09:56,200
Even their mother comes here every week.

1303
01:09:55,900 --> 01:09:57,890
The shop owner is an acquaintance.

1304
01:09:57,880 --> 01:10:00,230
Welcome.

1305
01:10:00,390 --> 01:10:01,650
Where's mom?

1306
01:10:01,640 --> 01:10:03,850
She's at home.

1307
01:10:03,840 --> 01:10:10,090
Did you and your brother come alone?
What a smart kid.

1308
01:10:08,280 --> 01:10:10,310
What did you come here to buy?

1309
01:10:10,300 --> 01:10:11,220
Flowers.

1310
01:10:11,210 --> 01:10:12,290
For dad?

1311
01:10:12,280 --> 01:10:16,540
Everyone remembers that his dad used to come here.

1312
01:10:16,530 --> 01:10:21,440
Carnations, lillies and sunflowers.
They have all kinds of flowers.

1313
01:10:21,430 --> 01:10:25,140
The shop owner is making them a bouquet.

1314
01:10:25,130 --> 01:10:27,270
Is there any color you would like to add?

1315
01:10:27,520 --> 01:10:28,360
Red.

1316
01:10:28,350 --> 01:10:30,180
Red, right?

1317
01:10:30,280 --> 01:10:31,090
Like this.

1318
01:10:31,080 --> 01:10:35,180
I see. Adding red has made is livelier.

1319
01:10:35,260 --> 01:10:38,100
The big brother has a nice taste.

1320
01:10:38,090 --> 01:10:41,960
Please add a pink ribbon for mom.

1321
01:10:41,950 --> 01:10:43,480
For mom, right?

1322
01:10:43,470 --> 01:10:47,220
That's what his father used to do too.

1323
01:10:47,210 --> 01:10:48,840
This flower?

1324
01:10:48,830 --> 01:10:52,130
He decided without any hesitation.

1325
01:10:48,830 --> 01:10:52,130
Will you give this to your mother?

1326
01:10:52,120 --> 01:10:53,880
I will wrap it for you.

1327
01:10:53,870 --> 01:10:56,190
Yellow is his little brothers favorite color.

1328
01:10:56,180 --> 01:10:57,740
Cute.

1329
01:10:57,730 --> 01:10:59,290
Aren't they?

1330
01:11:00,860 --> 01:11:03,370
Since they are a present.

1331
01:11:03,360 --> 01:11:08,680
The ones he chose were alstroemeria.
Also called Lily of the Incas.

1332
01:11:08,670 --> 01:11:12,100
The old man is even giving him a card to write on.

1333
01:11:12,090 --> 01:11:14,650
He can even write?

1334
01:11:12,780 --> 01:11:15,270
- He can write?
- That's amazing.

1335
01:11:15,440 --> 01:11:17,110
What is he writing?

1336
01:11:16,380 --> 01:11:17,760
- What is this?
- No clue.

1337
01:11:17,360 --> 01:11:19,060
What are you writing?

1338
01:11:19,050 --> 01:11:21,060
Thank you.

1339
01:11:21,620 --> 01:11:23,480
I can write it for you.

1340
01:11:23,470 --> 01:11:24,720
It said thank you?

1341
01:11:25,150 --> 01:11:28,330
The man wrote thanks to the mother.

1342
01:11:28,320 --> 01:11:29,410
Dad.

1343
01:11:29,400 --> 01:11:30,790
Also to your dad?

1344
01:11:30,780 --> 01:11:33,510
And thanks to his little brother too.

1345
01:11:33,500 --> 01:11:35,250
Hand it over both of you.

1346
01:11:35,240 --> 01:11:37,430
Thank you.

1347
01:11:36,570 --> 01:11:37,430
you.

1348
01:11:37,420 --> 01:11:38,620
Take care.

1349
01:11:38,610 --> 01:11:40,580
Be back tomorrow.

1350
01:11:40,570 --> 01:11:42,920
Back tomorrow?

1351
01:11:43,170 --> 01:11:48,530
There's only an hour left before the bus departs.
And they have to purchase some things first.

1352
01:11:48,520 --> 01:11:54,930
The supermarket is next to the bus terminal.
What they are getting is coffee and udon noodles.

1353
01:11:54,920 --> 01:11:57,010
Hurry up, Kanaya.

1354
01:11:57,000 --> 01:11:58,550
Hurry.

1355
01:11:58,540 --> 01:12:01,160
They've started going up the hill.

1356
01:12:01,150 --> 01:12:03,160
Even if he is asked to hurry...

1357
01:12:04,110 --> 01:12:06,180
Kanaya.

1358
01:12:06,170 --> 01:12:10,870
They haven't noticed when going by car
but it's pretty steep.

1359
01:12:10,860 --> 01:12:12,500
This way.

1360
01:12:12,490 --> 01:12:15,050
This won't work.

1361
01:12:13,370 --> 01:12:14,840
Do your best.

1362
01:12:15,040 --> 01:12:17,750
They won't make it at this pace.

1363
01:12:17,740 --> 01:12:20,830
Kanaya.

1364
01:12:20,820 --> 01:12:23,430
Give it all you got.

1365
01:12:23,420 --> 01:12:30,600
No matter how much you shout for this 2 year old who just spoke his first words he doesn't know what "hurry" means.

1366
01:12:30,590 --> 01:12:33,990
But he is properly walking above the holes.

1367
01:12:33,240 --> 01:12:34,010
I see.

1368
01:12:33,870 --> 01:12:35,050
Adhering to the rule

1369
01:12:35,040 --> 01:12:37,240
This way he won't walk into the street.

1370
01:12:37,230 --> 01:12:41,850
His brother has decided to leave him behind.

1371
01:12:40,110 --> 01:12:41,850
Is that okay?

1372
01:12:41,840 --> 01:12:44,710
I will go by myself.

1373
01:12:44,700 --> 01:12:51,870
They won't make it at this pace.
He has decided to go shopping ahead of his little brother.

1374
01:12:51,860 --> 01:12:55,620
Over the holes. Over the holes.

1375
01:12:55,610 --> 01:12:57,800
The supermarket is within sight.

1376
01:12:58,720 --> 01:12:59,880
I'm sweating.

1377
01:12:59,870 --> 01:13:02,190
The road is flat here.

1378
01:13:02,230 --> 01:13:04,440
The supermarket is right there.

1379
01:13:04,430 --> 01:13:07,930
This is a large-sized supermarket.

1380
01:13:07,920 --> 01:13:10,740
At this moment how is Kanaya doing?

1381
01:13:10,730 --> 01:13:17,130
With two traffic lights ahead of him if he walks
above the holes he will reach up with his brother.

1382
01:13:14,300 --> 01:13:15,130
Move forward.

1383
01:13:17,800 --> 01:13:24,330
But there's only 30 minutes before the bus leaves.
Will they make it?

1384
01:13:19,720 --> 01:13:20,450
Oh no.

1385
01:13:24,320 --> 01:13:26,180
The big brother has arrived.

1386
01:13:26,170 --> 01:13:28,180
I would like some coffee.

1387
01:13:28,170 --> 01:13:29,810
Concentrated coffee?

1388
01:13:29,800 --> 01:13:33,960
He found the coffee at the beverage aisle.

1389
01:13:33,950 --> 01:13:35,960
Is your mother looking for this?

1390
01:13:35,950 --> 01:13:38,700
Only for dad.

1391
01:13:35,950 --> 01:13:38,700
Only for dad?

1392
01:13:38,690 --> 01:13:40,870
Smokes and coffee reminds them of dad.

1393
01:13:42,220 --> 01:13:47,050
And there must also be some udon here.

1394
01:13:47,040 --> 01:13:50,370
He remembers well always getting these with his mother.

1395
01:13:50,360 --> 01:13:52,370
His little brother loves udon.

1396
01:13:56,120 --> 01:13:57,320
Heavy.

1397
01:13:57,310 --> 01:14:00,500
Is it really that heavy?

1398
01:14:00,490 --> 01:14:01,780
I made it.

1399
01:14:02,760 --> 01:14:04,740
He found all he needs.

1400
01:14:04,730 --> 01:14:07,430
I wonder how Kanaya is doing.

1401
01:14:08,230 --> 01:14:12,450
He was told to walk on the bumpy lines after the holes.

1402
01:14:11,520 --> 01:14:12,440
I see.

1403
01:14:12,430 --> 01:14:14,710
The supermarket is within sight.

1404
01:14:13,120 --> 01:14:14,000
Great.

1405
01:14:13,600 --> 01:14:14,710
It's straight ahead.

1406
01:14:14,700 --> 01:14:16,710
Where's brobro?

1407
01:14:17,130 --> 01:14:19,810
Brobro is still in the supermarket.

1408
01:14:19,800 --> 01:14:22,900
Putting all the items in the backpack.

1409
01:14:22,890 --> 01:14:25,280
Thank you very much.

1410
01:14:25,270 --> 01:14:27,810
Time will run out if you don't hurry.

1411
01:14:27,800 --> 01:14:30,090
- Better hurry.
- Hurry.

1412
01:14:30,120 --> 01:14:34,230
It's 10 minutes to and people have started gathering.

1413
01:14:34,220 --> 01:14:36,460
Where's Kanaya.

1414
01:14:36,580 --> 01:14:42,390
He believes Kanaya has kept walking far ahead.

1415
01:14:42,380 --> 01:14:44,760
He should be around here.

1416
01:14:44,750 --> 01:14:46,370
And at that time.

1417
01:14:46,360 --> 01:14:48,470
Brobro.

1418
01:14:48,460 --> 01:14:50,210
It's Kanaya.

1419
01:14:51,000 --> 01:14:52,290
He's calling.

1420
01:14:52,280 --> 01:14:55,140
Where are you? Where are you?

1421
01:14:53,830 --> 01:14:54,790
Where?

1422
01:14:55,160 --> 01:14:57,590
Kanaya.

1423
01:14:57,580 --> 01:14:58,970
Brobro.

1424
01:15:00,110 --> 01:15:02,420
Found him.

1425
01:15:02,410 --> 01:15:06,410
Just like his brother believed.

1426
01:15:04,660 --> 01:15:06,360
Amazing.

1427
01:15:06,390 --> 01:15:08,430
Brobro.

1428
01:15:08,420 --> 01:15:11,400
Isn't it nice that he can say brobro now.

1429
01:15:11,390 --> 01:15:15,910
I got coffee and udon.

1430
01:15:14,460 --> 01:15:15,910
He's talking normally to him.

1431
01:15:15,900 --> 01:15:17,740
Udon and coffee.

1432
01:15:20,430 --> 01:15:25,280
Come to the bus stop.

1433
01:15:25,940 --> 01:15:28,930
The little brother is amazing.

1434
01:15:30,700 --> 01:15:34,890
Kanaya, do your best.

1435
01:15:34,880 --> 01:15:36,090
Amazing.

1436
01:15:35,760 --> 01:15:41,290
Finally leaving the bumpy lines they get together for an emotional meet up.

1437
01:15:41,280 --> 01:15:42,700
Kanaya.

1438
01:15:42,890 --> 01:15:46,640
He really did his best not to cry.

1439
01:15:44,510 --> 01:15:46,520
Remarkable.

1440
01:15:46,760 --> 01:15:49,750
What? Aren't we going to hold hands?

1441
01:15:49,810 --> 01:15:51,560
He clearly put out his hands.

1442
01:15:50,830 --> 01:15:56,630
Since he made it this far by himself he wants his brother to finish on his own. Like a father.

1443
01:15:56,650 --> 01:16:01,090
They made it just in time with 5 minutes to spare.

1444
01:15:59,690 --> 01:16:01,850
They gave it their all.

1445
01:16:06,190 --> 01:16:15,210
The bus home doesn't have tinted windows.
With this we should be able to see the two from outside.

1446
01:16:16,760 --> 01:16:23,340
Back to the cameraman who waited for over 2 hours
he put a lot of care into getting a glimpse of the two.

1447
01:16:17,100 --> 01:16:22,470
Original Song:
藤田麻衣子 - 素敵なことがあなたを待っている

1448
01:16:21,820 --> 01:16:23,590
Do you best.

1449
01:16:23,580 --> 01:16:27,100
Where are they? Huh, they aren't there?

1450
01:16:27,460 --> 01:16:33,190
Can't see them cause they are asleep.
Even big brother.

1451
01:16:33,180 --> 01:16:36,450
From all the stress surrounding the trip.

1452
01:16:39,790 --> 01:16:45,470
In the end we didn't get a single glimpse of them going either of the directions.

1453
01:16:45,460 --> 01:16:51,050
It's the bus stop after crossing the river.
If they don't wake up they will go all the way to the mountains.

1454
01:16:52,930 --> 01:16:57,490
Their mother is waiting at the bus stop.

1455
01:16:57,480 --> 01:17:01,150
She's wondering if they made it to the bus.

1456
01:17:02,510 --> 01:17:06,290
They did.

1457
01:17:04,540 --> 01:17:06,280
Sound asleep.

1458
01:17:07,000 --> 01:17:09,470
It's coming.

1459
01:17:20,030 --> 01:17:21,960
- Are there any kids on board?
- Yes.

1460
01:17:21,950 --> 01:17:23,950
- Can I take a look?
- You're welcome.

1461
01:17:23,940 --> 01:17:27,320
- Must be asleep.
- I bet they are.

1462
01:17:27,850 --> 01:17:29,680
There they are.

1463
01:17:30,180 --> 01:17:33,620
Could you please wait a little bit longer?

1464
01:17:33,610 --> 01:17:36,360
Kanaya who kept walking above the holes.

1465
01:17:36,810 --> 01:17:38,150
Shuuya.

1466
01:17:38,140 --> 01:17:40,390
Shuuya who has become brobro.

1467
01:17:40,380 --> 01:17:42,190
You've arrived.

1468
01:17:41,050 --> 01:17:42,490
He gave it all he had.

1469
01:17:42,480 --> 01:17:44,490
He looks so surprised.

1470
01:17:44,920 --> 01:17:48,050
Mom, did you come all the way to get us?

1471
01:17:48,040 --> 01:17:54,030
Exactly 280 yen. Thank you for taking care of us. Ah, and I'm sorry it dragged out.

1472
01:17:54,020 --> 01:17:56,730
She also thanks the other riders.

1473
01:18:01,500 --> 01:18:03,930
Hold up. It wasn't just a dream?

1474
01:18:04,840 --> 01:18:07,150
I really did go on an errand.

1475
01:18:07,140 --> 01:18:10,340
It's fine. He even brought proof.

1476
01:18:12,220 --> 01:18:18,150
Amazing. Are these flowers for dad?
And are these for mom?

1477
01:18:18,140 --> 01:18:20,240
Why did you write here?

1478
01:18:20,230 --> 01:18:23,370
Just to make you happy.

1479
01:18:23,360 --> 01:18:24,810
Thank you very much.

1480
01:18:24,800 --> 01:18:32,790
I wrote it to you, mom. And also for dad.

1481
01:18:24,800 --> 01:18:32,790
Thank you. I saw it. Also for dad.

1482
01:18:32,780 --> 01:18:37,260
Dad, they've become able to purchase flowers.

1483
01:18:37,250 --> 01:18:39,170
Let's eat udon with broth.

1484
01:18:39,160 --> 01:18:42,340
Her laughter has returned to her voice.

1485
01:18:42,330 --> 01:18:43,710
Here you go.

1486
01:18:43,700 --> 01:18:49,060
And Kanaya has started speaking. He said "brobro".

1487
01:18:49,050 --> 01:18:53,010
As usual next to their father you find flowers and coffee.

1488
01:18:53,000 --> 01:18:58,910
Father, let's depend on big brother to bring you flowers.

1489
01:18:59,500 --> 01:19:06,250
Father lives on inside both of Shuuya and Kanaya.

1490
01:19:26,370 --> 01:19:30,200
- What a perfect errand.
- That's true.

1491
01:19:30,190 --> 01:19:36,340
At the beginning when the mother was standing strong I thought what a hard mother.

1492
01:19:36,330 --> 01:19:37,270
Well said.

1493
01:19:37,260 --> 01:19:45,870
I thought what a hard-disciplining mother
but then it turned out that she was kind.

1494
01:19:45,860 --> 01:19:51,990
I cried a lot. Especially considering the younger is 2 years old and staying by his brothers side.

1495
01:19:51,980 --> 01:19:58,090
I think that boys have a strong feeling towards wanting to protect their mother.

1496
01:19:58,080 --> 01:20:01,790
Such as wanting to be helpful to their mother.

1497
01:20:01,780 --> 01:20:08,610
And especially when there is a younger brother in play the older becomes aware of the role the play.

1498
01:20:08,600 --> 01:20:10,660
It was irresistible.

1499
01:20:10,650 --> 01:20:14,130
There was a big brother here who was crying a lot.

1500
01:20:12,540 --> 01:20:14,130
Wailing.

1501
01:20:14,120 --> 01:20:20,040
- I'm sorry. I just couldn't keep it in.
- I kept hearing "uuh uuh" next to me.

1502
01:20:20,030 --> 01:20:24,930
Seeing Shuuya was almost like watching myself.

1503
01:20:24,920 --> 01:20:25,940
Well brobro.

1504
01:20:25,930 --> 01:20:27,960
Don't be dumb.

1505
01:20:27,950 --> 01:20:31,970
But this is the first time I've been able to say it. Brobro.

1506
01:20:33,110 --> 01:20:36,360
- It's your first time saying it? I see.
- Brobro. Exactly.

1507
01:20:36,350 --> 01:20:40,090
Next will be our youngest to go on an errand for this time.

1508
01:20:40,080 --> 01:20:43,570
A small town called Nishiiya in the mountains of Shikoku.

1509
01:20:43,560 --> 01:20:47,950
A 2 year old and 2 months old will go on an errand.

1510
01:20:47,940 --> 01:20:56,120
If you go there you will notice that hardly any cars drive on the road. It's a very quiet place.

1511
01:20:56,110 --> 01:20:58,370
This is the only shop here.

1512
01:20:58,360 --> 01:21:05,290
Food, alcohol, soy sauce, tissues and even emergency drugs are available here.

1513
01:21:05,280 --> 01:21:07,290
The towns convenience store.

1514
01:21:08,010 --> 01:21:10,450
It's been in operation for 87 years.

1515
01:21:10,440 --> 01:21:18,600
This shop hasn't changed and people love it for it.
The ones running it are the Kitas.

1516
01:21:18,590 --> 01:21:25,930
Since this place is so safe and our kid is capable her mother has asked us to film the errand.

1517
01:21:28,280 --> 01:21:30,400
Say "welcome".

1518
01:21:31,590 --> 01:21:34,580
- No way.
- This kid?
- She's so small.

1519
01:21:33,560 --> 01:21:36,450
Isn't she just a toddler?

1520
01:21:34,870 --> 01:21:36,440
Can this kid do it?

1521
01:21:36,430 --> 01:21:38,060
Bread please.

1522
01:21:38,050 --> 01:21:41,450
We don't meet the children until the day of shooting.

1523
01:21:38,790 --> 01:21:43,140
Yumemi

1524
01:21:41,440 --> 01:21:45,380
Our program aims not to prefer any children over others.

1525
01:21:45,370 --> 01:21:48,660
Today we have Anpan bread.

1526
01:21:48,650 --> 01:21:50,490
She can talk.

1527
01:21:50,480 --> 01:21:53,900
Is it really this kid?
Not an older sister or something?

1528
01:21:53,890 --> 01:21:55,830
We called out the mother.

1529
01:21:57,500 --> 01:22:00,610
Is that kid Yumemi?

1530
01:22:01,280 --> 01:22:02,660
- Is it Yume?
- It's Yume.

1531
01:22:02,650 --> 01:22:05,090
- Isn't she too small?
- She's small?

1532
01:22:05,080 --> 01:22:09,240
- Can she go on an errand?
- An errand? Yeah, she's in a good mood today.

1533
01:22:09,230 --> 01:22:13,050
- Mood? Are you confident?
- Yes.

1534
01:22:13,040 --> 01:22:21,080
When I told her to go to the swings she ran towards it alone.

1535
01:22:21,070 --> 01:22:29,450
So it's really this kid. Since the 16 staffers came all the way from Tokyo let's just see how it plays out.

1536
01:22:29,440 --> 01:22:31,940
Poi.

1537
01:22:31,930 --> 01:22:33,330
She's cleaning up.

1538
01:22:33,320 --> 01:22:37,280
So many toys. The bag is going to be full.

1539
01:22:37,270 --> 01:22:40,610
Can it all fit in?

1540
01:22:37,270 --> 01:22:40,610
Yeah, this bag might not be enough.

1541
01:22:39,940 --> 01:22:41,870
She can conversate.

1542
01:22:40,600 --> 01:22:43,010
She understands quantities.

1543
01:22:43,000 --> 01:22:48,110
It won't be able to close.

1544
01:22:43,000 --> 01:22:48,110
Yeah, it won't. Do we have another bag?

1545
01:22:48,100 --> 01:22:51,000
Let's have a look if we do.

1546
01:22:51,580 --> 01:22:55,090
Will she be able to spot the right item.

1547
01:22:55,470 --> 01:22:57,880
There ain't one.

1548
01:22:57,030 --> 01:22:58,670
Ain't one?

1549
01:22:58,170 --> 01:23:01,240
We've probably run out.

1550
01:23:01,390 --> 01:23:02,550
What to do?

1551
01:23:02,540 --> 01:23:06,640
Even if asked such a question.
She's holding the remote to the AC.

1552
01:23:06,630 --> 01:23:09,360
Hello, Yu.

1553
01:23:06,630 --> 01:23:09,360
What?

1554
01:23:09,350 --> 01:23:11,880
I have a request to make.

1555
01:23:11,870 --> 01:23:17,210
Huh?

1556
01:23:11,870 --> 01:23:17,210
We've run out of bags.

1557
01:23:17,200 --> 01:23:24,650
