1558
01:23:24,640 --> 01:23:26,950
Yume will go buy them.

1559
01:23:26,940 --> 01:23:30,450
Will you buy them? Really?

1560
01:23:26,940 --> 01:23:30,450
Yes.

1561
01:23:30,440 --> 01:23:32,980
It's at the old man Kita's place.

1562
01:23:30,440 --> 01:23:32,980
Okay.

1563
01:23:32,970 --> 01:23:37,060
Pass the school, go up the hill and then buy it.
Are you up for it?

1564
01:23:37,050 --> 01:23:37,930
Yes.

1565
01:23:37,920 --> 01:23:41,300
A bag? Really?

1566
01:23:37,920 --> 01:23:41,300
Yes.

1567
01:23:41,290 --> 01:23:43,160
Can I really make this request?

1568
01:23:41,290 --> 01:23:43,160
Yes.

1569
01:23:43,150 --> 01:23:44,450
For real?

1570
01:23:45,220 --> 01:23:47,140
I have another request.

1571
01:23:47,130 --> 01:23:48,920
Another request?

1572
01:23:48,910 --> 01:23:50,230
I want this.

1573
01:23:50,220 --> 01:23:51,850
A toy egg.

1574
01:23:51,840 --> 01:23:54,100
It's an egg.

1575
01:23:51,840 --> 01:23:54,100
What's this?

1576
01:23:54,090 --> 01:23:59,570
I would also like eggs for todays lunch since we've run out. Can you do it?

1577
01:23:59,560 --> 01:24:01,070
Yes, of course.

1578
01:24:01,060 --> 01:24:04,680
It's the usual route to the shop.

1579
01:24:04,670 --> 01:24:09,410
She was asked to get bags and eggs.

1580
01:24:09,400 --> 01:24:11,430
We've left a camera on the floor.

1581
01:24:11,420 --> 01:24:13,890
Mom, eggs... wait what's that?

1582
01:24:13,880 --> 01:24:15,250
Immediately spotted it.

1583
01:24:15,040 --> 01:24:16,390
Amazing.

1584
01:24:15,240 --> 01:24:19,450
I guess it was left by a construction worker.

1585
01:24:15,240 --> 01:24:19,450
What is it?

1586
01:24:19,450 --> 01:24:20,680
Be careful.

1587
01:24:20,670 --> 01:24:23,300
Departure.

1588
01:24:20,670 --> 01:24:23,300
Yes, departing.

1589
01:24:23,290 --> 01:24:26,460
She has to sit on each step to go down the stairs.

1590
01:24:26,570 --> 01:24:30,480
Each step requires this much effort.

1591
01:24:30,470 --> 01:24:32,740
Take care.

1592
01:24:32,730 --> 01:24:34,690
Heading off.

1593
01:24:35,010 --> 01:24:39,210
The mother is a former Japanese teacher.
A real pro in education.

1594
01:24:39,200 --> 01:24:44,660
A besides bringing up a kid she's already brought up two older sisters.

1595
01:24:44,660 --> 01:24:52,960
And she has taught Yumemi that she can accomplish anything. She can even talk really well.

1596
01:24:56,330 --> 01:24:58,230
Wait, she stopped.

1597
01:24:58,220 --> 01:25:02,490
Sticking to the wall and checking out her surroundings.

1598
01:25:02,480 --> 01:25:04,770
Will she go back now?

1599
01:25:04,800 --> 01:25:06,870
She started moving.

1600
01:25:06,860 --> 01:25:09,990
Oh, she's going out after all.

1601
01:25:10,160 --> 01:25:13,990
She's cautious.

1602
01:25:14,680 --> 01:25:17,280
Yumemi is careful.

1603
01:25:21,000 --> 01:25:24,270
She has started spinning.

1604
01:25:24,260 --> 01:25:26,410
Spinning one round.

1605
01:25:27,380 --> 01:25:30,200
Then another.

1606
01:25:33,020 --> 01:25:34,130
Mama.

1607
01:25:34,120 --> 01:25:38,070
Mama? Will she go back home?

1608
01:25:34,780 --> 01:25:36,770
That makes sense.

1609
01:25:42,370 --> 01:25:44,710
She disappeared.

1610
01:25:56,950 --> 01:25:58,380
Where to?

1611
01:25:57,820 --> 01:26:02,520
She started climbing the hill.
This road leads to the shop.

1612
01:26:02,510 --> 01:26:08,010
She's putting all her power
into climbing the 13 degree slope.

1613
01:26:08,000 --> 01:26:09,930
She stopped.

1614
01:26:11,130 --> 01:26:12,380
It's her mama.

1615
01:26:12,370 --> 01:26:14,620
Ah, she's watching her.

1616
01:26:12,370 --> 01:26:14,620
Do your best.

1617
01:26:14,640 --> 01:26:17,140
Is she crying?

1618
01:26:17,950 --> 01:26:19,930
Do your best.

1619
01:26:20,130 --> 01:26:25,170
Do your best. Off you go.

1620
01:26:20,130 --> 01:26:25,170
The one crying is the mama.

1621
01:26:25,160 --> 01:26:26,890
Yumemi isn't crying.

1622
01:26:28,860 --> 01:26:30,710
Do your best.

1623
01:26:31,810 --> 01:26:34,720
One two. One two.

1624
01:26:35,330 --> 01:26:36,710
One two.

1625
01:26:36,700 --> 01:26:39,820
She suddenly turned her back and started picking her nose.

1626
01:26:39,810 --> 01:26:41,580
Departure.

1627
01:26:39,810 --> 01:26:41,580
Do your best.

1628
01:26:41,570 --> 01:26:45,360
Her mom isn't there to stop her from picking her nose.

1629
01:26:47,160 --> 01:26:51,810
She's really going for it.
We might've underestimated her.

1630
01:26:51,800 --> 01:26:54,630
Still going up the hill.

1631
01:26:55,050 --> 01:27:01,930
She stopped again.
Looking back at her home.

1632
01:27:04,510 --> 01:27:08,440
She's making a grimace.
Is she going to cry?

1633
01:27:08,430 --> 01:27:13,500
Her seeking pose.

1634
01:27:08,430 --> 01:27:13,500
Where is mama?

1635
01:27:13,490 --> 01:27:17,830
Her shouting out pose.

1636
01:27:13,490 --> 01:27:17,830
Mama.

1637
01:27:18,700 --> 01:27:20,280
She's so cute.

1638
01:27:20,750 --> 01:27:22,400
Mama.

1639
01:27:22,390 --> 01:27:26,180
All that searching and shouting out but mama isn't there.

1640
01:27:26,170 --> 01:27:28,370
She keeps searching.

1641
01:27:28,360 --> 01:27:33,510
This is her thinking pose.

1642
01:27:28,360 --> 01:27:33,510
What should I do. Mama...

1643
01:27:33,540 --> 01:27:35,890
She can't go home.

1644
01:27:37,420 --> 01:27:40,180
She's really going for it?

1645
01:27:40,170 --> 01:27:43,090
She's hard to read.

1646
01:27:43,080 --> 01:27:49,070
Yumemi has reached the top of the hill
and is heading for the shop.

1647
01:27:53,340 --> 01:27:57,420
She's greeting our traffic patrol.

1648
01:27:53,440 --> 01:27:55,360
Hello.

1649
01:27:57,410 --> 01:28:02,830
It's straight ahead. The shop's
red banner is visible from here.

1650
01:28:02,820 --> 01:28:05,800
I can see it too.

1651
01:28:06,350 --> 01:28:10,930
She knows to walk on the edge of the street.

1652
01:28:11,870 --> 01:28:18,160
She's walking on the stone lids
like her mother taught her

1653
01:28:18,750 --> 01:28:20,500
She stopped.

1654
01:28:21,370 --> 01:28:25,410
Oh, the cameraman was in the way.
We are sorry.

1655
01:28:27,480 --> 01:28:29,650
Did she fall?

1656
01:28:29,640 --> 01:28:37,960
No, she's just sitting. This is the usual spot she has a break when she's out walking with her mother.

1657
01:28:37,950 --> 01:28:40,880
Is it someone she knows?

1658
01:28:40,870 --> 01:28:43,920
The old lady of the health clinic.

1659
01:28:44,030 --> 01:28:50,130
She greets them every time they go for a walk.
And she's even bringing candy?

1660
01:28:50,470 --> 01:28:52,760
Here you go.

1661
01:28:50,470 --> 01:28:52,760
Thank you.

1662
01:28:52,750 --> 01:28:54,470
She knows to properly say thanks.

1663
01:28:54,460 --> 01:28:55,770
Here you go.

1664
01:28:55,760 --> 01:29:00,100
Her cherished Madeleine cakes.

1665
01:28:58,380 --> 01:29:00,010
This is the best.

1666
01:29:00,490 --> 01:29:02,020
Delicious?

1667
01:29:02,760 --> 01:29:04,610
Bye bye.

1668
01:29:02,760 --> 01:29:04,610
Bye bye.

1669
01:29:04,600 --> 01:29:11,270
Not only candy but watching and protecting from afar that's the love that goes around in this town.

1670
01:29:08,680 --> 01:29:09,640
Amazing.

1671
01:29:11,260 --> 01:29:14,190
I will keep walking.

1672
01:29:15,470 --> 01:29:20,550
After a short rest and she's ready to walk again.

1673
01:29:21,200 --> 01:29:25,700
There's a Madelaine crumb left on her cheeck.

1674
01:29:25,690 --> 01:29:27,880
She has arrived at the shop.

1675
01:29:27,870 --> 01:29:36,490
She was asked to get bags and eggs.
Coming from outside it's quite dark inside.

1676
01:29:36,480 --> 01:29:39,170
She's intimidated by going in.

1677
01:29:39,860 --> 01:29:43,300
Did you come by yourself? How clever you are.

1678
01:29:43,290 --> 01:29:46,040
What do you need?

1679
01:29:47,460 --> 01:29:51,740
Eggs? How many?

1680
01:29:51,730 --> 01:29:54,170
Two? Two eggs?

1681
01:29:54,160 --> 01:29:57,380
No way she can carry two containers.

1682
01:29:56,450 --> 01:29:57,420
No way.

1683
01:29:57,410 --> 01:30:02,520
But the old lady took out two eggs and placed them in a bag for her.

1684
01:30:01,360 --> 01:30:02,600
How kind.

1685
01:30:02,590 --> 01:30:05,540
Cause that's how they were sold in the old days.

1686
01:30:05,530 --> 01:30:10,030
They will never be able to sell this container.

1687
01:30:10,020 --> 01:30:12,760
The 83 year old husband.

1688
01:30:12,750 --> 01:30:14,020
Good morning.

1689
01:30:14,010 --> 01:30:16,740
Enjoy the conversation with this tiny customer.

1690
01:30:16,730 --> 01:30:22,190
Did you come alone? How clever you are.

1691
01:30:22,220 --> 01:30:23,960
She's being praised.

1692
01:30:24,550 --> 01:30:26,900
Getting eggs?

1693
01:30:26,890 --> 01:30:30,750
Mama loves them.

1694
01:30:26,890 --> 01:30:30,750
She does?

1695
01:30:32,590 --> 01:30:37,720
And she was able to come by herself.

1696
01:30:32,590 --> 01:30:37,720
She's become more conversational since last.

1697
01:30:37,710 --> 01:30:41,110
It's a frog.

1698
01:30:37,710 --> 01:30:41,110
Thank you.

1699
01:30:41,850 --> 01:30:43,510
What is this thing?

1700
01:30:43,500 --> 01:30:45,420
What is this thing?

1701
01:30:45,410 --> 01:30:53,960
2 years and 2 months and an 83 year old.
Their conversation tempo oddly suit each other.

1702
01:30:56,010 --> 01:30:58,170
She's so excited.

1703
01:30:58,210 --> 01:31:00,940
Yumemi, you still haven't finished the errand.

1704
01:31:00,930 --> 01:31:04,600
Yumemi, are you only getting eggs?

1705
01:31:04,590 --> 01:31:08,920
She's searching for the forgotten thing in her mind.

1706
01:31:08,910 --> 01:31:11,330
What did mama ask you to buy?

1707
01:31:11,320 --> 01:31:13,490
And bags too.

1708
01:31:13,480 --> 01:31:15,170
She remembered.

1709
01:31:15,160 --> 01:31:22,920
When she's asked she will remember.
The old lady brings out the bags for her.

1710
01:31:22,910 --> 01:31:25,900
She also knows that she needs to pay.

1711
01:31:25,890 --> 01:31:26,810
Here.

1712
01:31:26,800 --> 01:31:30,980
Putting out 500 yen and getting her money back. She did it.

1713
01:31:30,970 --> 01:31:32,200
Praiseworthy.

1714
01:31:32,430 --> 01:31:34,530
I will give you this.

1715
01:31:34,520 --> 01:31:38,590
Thank you for saying thank you.

1716
01:31:34,520 --> 01:31:38,590
Thank you.

1717
01:31:38,580 --> 01:31:41,600
Thank you for saying thank you.

1718
01:31:41,590 --> 01:31:45,690
To avoid the eggs from cracking he puts them in her purse.

1719
01:31:45,690 --> 01:31:47,310
Safe.

1720
01:31:45,690 --> 01:31:48,250
Say your goodbyes.

1721
01:31:48,240 --> 01:31:51,600
Bye bye.

1722
01:31:48,240 --> 01:31:51,600
Bye bye.

1723
01:31:51,850 --> 01:31:54,420
She won't say goodbye?

1724
01:31:55,100 --> 01:31:57,500
Bye bye.

1725
01:31:55,100 --> 01:31:57,500
Bye bye.

1726
01:31:56,880 --> 01:31:58,840
Doesn't want to go home.

1727
01:31:57,490 --> 01:32:01,910
While they say goodbye the old man slowly moves away.

1728
01:32:01,900 --> 01:32:03,600
Will you be fine?

1729
01:32:04,730 --> 01:32:09,690
Yumemi finds it hard to go away.

1730
01:32:08,040 --> 01:32:11,610
-What a weird scene.

- Gramps be careful of things behind you.

1731
01:32:14,720 --> 01:32:15,800
What?

1732
01:32:15,790 --> 01:32:20,020
The old man is now much further away.

1733
01:32:19,100 --> 01:32:22,410
This is quite moving.

1734
01:32:26,200 --> 01:32:30,320
And with that the old man...

1735
01:32:30,310 --> 01:32:33,930
disappears from view.

1736
01:32:32,030 --> 01:32:34,450
Their bond is so strong.

1737
01:32:33,920 --> 01:32:38,890
Alright Yumemi, that was the goodbye.

1738
01:32:38,880 --> 01:32:43,590
After having so much fun she remembers her mother.

1739
01:32:43,580 --> 01:32:45,700
Mama.

1740
01:32:44,550 --> 01:32:46,900
That's right.

1741
01:32:49,340 --> 01:32:51,450
Do your best.

1742
01:32:54,590 --> 01:32:58,650
She's taking a secret shortcut through the school.

1743
01:32:58,640 --> 01:33:00,390
She knows about this?

1744
01:33:00,950 --> 01:33:02,530
Amazing.

1745
01:33:02,520 --> 01:33:06,280
She can see her home from here.

1746
01:33:07,660 --> 01:33:10,820
Her mother can see someone in pink clothes.

1747
01:33:10,810 --> 01:33:13,540
Yu.

1748
01:33:13,530 --> 01:33:15,250
Oh, mama.

1749
01:33:15,240 --> 01:33:16,410
Welcome home.

1750
01:33:16,400 --> 01:33:20,090
I'm home. I brought the bags.

1751
01:33:20,080 --> 01:33:24,290
Sorry for keeping you waiting.

1752
01:33:27,000 --> 01:33:32,810
Her mother thinks she forgot all about the eggs.

1753
01:33:37,110 --> 01:33:39,290
Thank you.

1754
01:33:38,520 --> 01:33:40,430
Amazing.

1755
01:33:40,420 --> 01:33:42,410
Both the kid and the mom are.

1756
01:33:42,400 --> 01:33:46,750
One by one she climbs the stairs with all her might.

1757
01:33:46,740 --> 01:33:49,290
The goal is her mothers arms.

1758
01:33:49,280 --> 01:33:53,740
Thank you for getting it for me. Welcome home.

1759
01:33:55,830 --> 01:33:59,830
I'm home.

1760
01:33:55,830 --> 01:33:59,830
Welcome home. Thank you.

1761
01:33:59,820 --> 01:34:02,490
You got the bags for me?

1762
01:34:02,480 --> 01:34:04,150
And you forgot the eggs?

1763
01:34:04,140 --> 01:34:05,860
Yes.

1764
01:34:05,890 --> 01:34:07,270
I have them.

1765
01:34:07,260 --> 01:34:09,960
You do? Where are they?

1766
01:34:09,950 --> 01:34:12,310
Are they in there?

1767
01:34:09,950 --> 01:34:12,310
Here.

1768
01:34:12,300 --> 01:34:14,520
Open.

1769
01:34:16,120 --> 01:34:17,680
What's this?

1770
01:34:19,890 --> 01:34:22,050
Amazing. Amazing.

1771
01:34:24,130 --> 01:34:26,040
These are the eggs.

1772
01:34:26,030 --> 01:34:29,550
They are in there and they didn't crack.

1773
01:34:29,540 --> 01:34:32,630
All thanks to the old man.

1774
01:34:32,620 --> 01:34:34,710
What will we make with these today?

1775
01:34:35,580 --> 01:34:37,380
Don't do that. They will break.

1776
01:34:37,370 --> 01:34:39,650
Since these are eggs.

1777
01:34:39,640 --> 01:34:41,130
Since these are eggs.

1778
01:34:41,120 --> 01:34:42,210
Do it.

1779
01:34:42,200 --> 01:34:45,170
Cracking the eggs for lunch.

1780
01:34:47,900 --> 01:34:48,780
You did it.

1781
01:34:48,770 --> 01:34:52,930
Made omurice with the eggs.

1782
01:34:51,650 --> 01:34:52,930
How nice.

1783
01:34:52,920 --> 01:34:54,930
Thanks for the meal.

1784
01:34:57,350 --> 01:35:01,540
Yu, the eggs you bought are delicious. They really are.

1785
01:35:01,550 --> 01:35:07,500
That's nice. But Yumemi isn't putting the eggs in her mouth.

1786
01:35:06,390 --> 01:35:07,930
Why?

1787
01:35:07,920 --> 01:35:09,880
No go.

1788
01:35:07,920 --> 01:35:09,880
Say aah.

1789
01:35:09,870 --> 01:35:11,630
Are you sure?

1790
01:35:11,620 --> 01:35:14,040
Here you go.

1791
01:35:11,620 --> 01:35:14,040
Mama can have it.

1792
01:35:14,530 --> 01:35:17,570
I want mama to enjoy it all.

1793
01:35:18,090 --> 01:35:21,930
Since she purchased it just for mama.

1794
01:35:23,290 --> 01:35:31,420
Todays noon nap. I wonder if she's
talking to the old man in her dreams.

1795
01:35:34,080 --> 01:35:35,460
The mother is amazing.

1796
01:35:35,450 --> 01:35:39,880
Isn't she? I've never seen a 2 year old like this.

1797
01:35:39,870 --> 01:35:42,100
The only one who cried was the mom.

1798
01:35:42,090 --> 01:35:46,970
The bye bye scene with the old man too.
The way he stepped back.

1799
01:35:46,960 --> 01:35:49,590
First time seeing an old guy doing the moonwalk.

1800
01:35:49,580 --> 01:35:51,140
Old guy moonwalk?

1801
01:35:51,130 --> 01:35:58,820
A 2 year 2 month year old who can talk this well while she can hardly descend stairs

1802
01:35:58,810 --> 01:36:02,170
both the mom and Yumemi are remarkable.

1803
01:36:02,160 --> 01:36:03,010
Right.

1804
01:36:03,000 --> 01:36:05,340
The "open" reveal was amazing as well.

1805
01:36:05,330 --> 01:36:09,520
It was like a magic show. Open. So cute.

1806
01:36:09,590 --> 01:36:12,790
I was worried about the eggs after all that hugging.

1807
01:36:12,780 --> 01:36:13,780
At the end yeah.

1808
01:36:13,770 --> 01:36:15,780
She was going like this.

1809
01:36:15,770 --> 01:36:17,970
And the "sorry for keeping you waiting".

1810
01:36:17,960 --> 01:36:24,010
Saying "sorry for keeping you waiting" and "open" such precious grown up words.

1811
01:36:24,000 --> 01:36:26,550
Sorry for keeping you waiting...

1812
01:36:26,540 --> 01:36:30,010
Sugiyama how are you feeling right now?

1813
01:36:30,000 --> 01:36:36,450
Watching the previous segments they are all full of drama

1814
01:36:30,000 --> 01:36:40,090
Sugiyamas kid will go on an errand now.

1815
01:36:36,440 --> 01:36:42,700
but after my son came back I kept asking how it was but he didn't tell me much.

1816
01:36:42,690 --> 01:36:47,030
so it will be my first time seeing it today.
I wonder how it will be.

1817
01:36:47,020 --> 01:36:48,080
- Excited?
- Excited?

1818
01:36:48,070 --> 01:36:49,420
I'm really looking forward.

1819
01:36:49,410 --> 01:36:56,440
Sugiyama mama please introduce the clip.

1820
01:36:56,430 --> 01:37:01,690
