1821
01:37:02,810 --> 01:37:08,250
Ai Sugiyama who reached the world No. 1 in women's doubles.

1822
01:37:06,390 --> 01:37:08,250
No. 1 in the world is impressive.

1823
01:37:08,240 --> 01:37:13,490
She won 3 grand slams in the doubles.

1824
01:37:10,950 --> 01:37:12,620
Amazing.

1825
01:37:13,480 --> 01:37:18,190
Having reached the No. 1 ranking she is called The Super Woman by the tennis world.

1826
01:37:18,180 --> 01:37:25,160
She had 62 consecutive Grand Slam main draw appearances which won her a guiness record.

1827
01:37:25,150 --> 01:37:31,550
In 2009 she retired from her 17 year old tennis career.

1828
01:37:31,740 --> 01:37:34,250
Her husband is a former pro-golfer.

1829
01:37:34,240 --> 01:37:38,300
Even though he is Japanese he was born and raised in Kenya.

1830
01:37:38,290 --> 01:37:41,210
Now he's Ai's manager.

1831
01:37:41,200 --> 01:37:45,990
Here is Yuu who is 3 years and 8 months old and who loves to play with balls.

1832
01:37:45,980 --> 01:37:49,450
Wonder which one of the parents he is taking after?

1833
01:37:50,330 --> 01:37:54,830
Let's first see him play golf with his father.

1834
01:37:57,270 --> 01:37:59,140
Is he a golfer?

1835
01:37:59,530 --> 01:38:00,760
Amazing.

1836
01:38:00,750 --> 01:38:03,590
Or is he a tennis player?

1837
01:38:06,060 --> 01:38:07,110
Well done.

1838
01:38:07,100 --> 01:38:09,690
He has his game face on.

1839
01:38:10,660 --> 01:38:12,530
Okay, next is mommy.

1840
01:38:12,520 --> 01:38:15,080
Ai's tennis club.

1841
01:38:15,070 --> 01:38:22,850
It only felt naturally to have the errand
be centered around this place.

1842
01:38:22,840 --> 01:38:25,330
We want him to always face challenges.

1843
01:38:22,880 --> 01:38:27,260
Sugiyamas 3 rules to bringing up a kid

1844
01:38:25,320 --> 01:38:31,910
It's the first step to accomplish things so that's why we put stress on seriously faces challenges.

1845
01:38:31,900 --> 01:38:38,740
Next is not putting limits to their ability
if I keep telling them that they can't do X thing

1846
01:38:39,730 --> 01:38:48,090
that will really destroy the will of my child so instead I will tell them that I believe in them.

1847
01:38:48,080 --> 01:38:51,090
And the last one is as expected: Waiting.

1848
01:38:51,080 --> 01:38:55,400
Those are some splendid rules but some rules are meant to be broken.

1849
01:38:55,390 --> 01:38:56,630
They aren't.

1850
01:38:56,620 --> 01:39:00,190
Like making him eat without waiting after saying "Hurry up and eat".

1851
01:39:00,180 --> 01:39:02,480
There is a big gap between reality and the ideal.

1852
01:39:02,470 --> 01:39:08,580
And at the club they make him help them out such as picking up balls on the court.

1853
01:39:08,570 --> 01:39:11,030
You are almost done. Once you are done come to us.

1854
01:39:11,530 --> 01:39:14,050
Not putting limits on their ability.

1855
01:39:14,040 --> 01:39:16,360
I will be exhausted if I do it alone.

1856
01:39:16,350 --> 01:39:19,560
You will but you are almost done.

1857
01:39:19,550 --> 01:39:21,120
I wanna do it with mama.

1858
01:39:21,110 --> 01:39:23,050
Okay but only 3 balls.

1859
01:39:23,040 --> 01:39:27,420
Hasn't she just been made to pick up balls by her son?

1860
01:39:26,910 --> 01:39:28,930
What was the meaning of this?

1861
01:39:27,850 --> 01:39:30,430
Yuu easily got away with that.

1862
01:39:30,420 --> 01:39:35,150
The dad has a theory on why it's hard to accomplish the ideal.

1863
01:39:35,140 --> 01:39:39,880
There's a gap between what he is being told and what he wants to do.

1864
01:39:39,870 --> 01:39:46,090
That's right. But it takes time to realize.

1865
01:39:46,080 --> 01:39:50,010
- I am the one who is best put together.
- No way.

1866
01:39:50,000 --> 01:39:54,740
That's what I think.

1867
01:39:56,600 --> 01:40:00,720
They cuddle him while being being afraid of breaking his back.

1868
01:40:00,710 --> 01:40:05,890
The mom has thought of a plan
to make him want to go on an errand.

1869
01:40:05,880 --> 01:40:10,210
If we directly ask him to do it tomorrow he probably won't.

1870
01:40:10,200 --> 01:40:16,650
It's not about having him do warm ups but we need to give him the resolution to accomplish it.

1871
01:40:16,640 --> 01:40:19,700
With resolution is how you greet the world.

1872
01:40:19,760 --> 01:40:21,990
Will it be fine?

1873
01:40:20,650 --> 01:40:23,170
Is dad missing the resolution?

1874
01:40:23,160 --> 01:40:25,170
I'm crying now.

1875
01:40:25,160 --> 01:40:28,200
What kind of tears are those?

1876
01:40:26,250 --> 01:40:28,820
He cries so easily.

1877
01:40:28,200 --> 01:40:30,780
I am so nervous.

1878
01:40:31,860 --> 01:40:36,050
He said he's the best put together of the two. Ai seems to be the one.

1879
01:40:36,420 --> 01:40:40,440
It's finally the day of the errand.

1880
01:40:40,430 --> 01:40:43,890
They have made him help out extra for a month.

1881
01:40:43,880 --> 01:40:46,330
- Good morning.
- Look at this.

1882
01:40:46,320 --> 01:40:48,550
It's still dirty over there.

1883
01:40:48,540 --> 01:40:49,570
I know that.

1884
01:40:49,560 --> 01:40:54,360
One whole month of this kind of exchange.
He must be ready to prove himself helpful.

1885
01:40:54,350 --> 01:40:56,090
This helps a lot.

1886
01:40:56,160 --> 01:40:58,150
He enjoys being praised.

1887
01:40:58,140 --> 01:41:00,250
- He's so determend.
- Nice.

1888
01:41:00,240 --> 01:41:02,290
Okay.

1889
01:41:00,240 --> 01:41:02,290
Okay.

1890
01:41:02,280 --> 01:41:05,480
Thank you. It's become really clean.

1891
01:41:06,180 --> 01:41:10,840
The balls are all over the 4th tennis court if you could...

1892
01:41:10,830 --> 01:41:13,060
Okay, let's go after putting the brooms back.

1893
01:41:13,050 --> 01:41:16,280
Hurrying to the fourth court.

1894
01:41:16,270 --> 01:41:17,960
- Nice.
- Amazing.

1895
01:41:18,880 --> 01:41:21,490
The face of a working man.

1896
01:41:21,480 --> 01:41:26,410
Not pretending to help but actually being helpful.

1897
01:41:27,810 --> 01:41:29,280
Thank you.

1898
01:41:30,440 --> 01:41:32,690
Thank you.

1899
01:41:33,650 --> 01:41:35,900
I did it all.

1900
01:41:35,990 --> 01:41:39,000
Thank you. You helped out everyone.

1901
01:41:38,990 --> 01:41:40,440
Yep.

1902
01:41:40,650 --> 01:41:48,050
He has come to appreciate helping others out.
He's ready since the cherry blossom has bloomed at the club.

1903
01:41:48,040 --> 01:41:56,200
They have a cherry blossom viewing party every year.
And this year they have a special cake to go with it.

1904
01:41:56,600 --> 01:42:00,800
And with this cake the errand begins.

1905
01:42:00,790 --> 01:42:02,270
It's amazing.

1906
01:42:02,260 --> 01:42:03,410
A racket?

1907
01:42:03,400 --> 01:42:05,350
Do you remember it, Yuu?

1908
01:42:05,430 --> 01:42:07,590
The racket is made from chocolate.

1909
01:42:07,580 --> 01:42:12,050
Same racket that mom used to play with.

1910
01:42:07,580 --> 01:42:12,050
That's what it is!

1911
01:42:12,040 --> 01:42:16,390
It's the same type of racket that Ai was using as a player.

1912
01:42:17,040 --> 01:42:22,760
She sent the racket to the cakemaker
and they created a replica.

1913
01:42:22,750 --> 01:42:28,740
And the father left the racket at the cake shop on purpose.

1914
01:42:28,730 --> 01:42:30,460
Where's the racket?

1915
01:42:30,450 --> 01:42:32,010
The racket? Here.

1916
01:42:32,000 --> 01:42:33,940
No no, the real racket.

1917
01:42:33,930 --> 01:42:37,630
The theatrics have begun.

1918
01:42:38,110 --> 01:42:41,670
I mistakenly left it at the cake shop.

1919
01:42:41,760 --> 01:42:44,770
He's saying that he forgot it. This is terrible.

1920
01:42:44,780 --> 01:42:47,550
Without it you can't play tennis.

1921
01:42:47,540 --> 01:42:51,030
- That's right. This is no good.
- We're in trouble.

1922
01:42:51,460 --> 01:42:53,340
I forgot it.

1923
01:42:53,400 --> 01:42:55,800
I'm begging of you. Can you bring it?

1924
01:42:55,790 --> 01:42:58,230
I will? All by myself?

1925
01:42:58,220 --> 01:43:00,060
You can do it.

1926
01:43:00,050 --> 01:43:03,590
Is it okay if it's lost? It's my most precious racket.

1927
01:43:03,580 --> 01:43:06,110
I used it when I was a player.

1928
01:43:06,950 --> 01:43:11,750
That's right.

1929
01:43:06,950 --> 01:43:11,750
Will I go all by myself? But that's a first.

1930
01:43:11,740 --> 01:43:13,140
You can do it.

1931
01:43:13,130 --> 01:43:16,910
How come?

1932
01:43:13,130 --> 01:43:16,910
I don't want to do it.

1933
01:43:16,900 --> 01:43:20,850
I'm sleepy.

1934
01:43:16,900 --> 01:43:20,850
Sleepy? So for the party...

1935
01:43:20,840 --> 01:43:22,510
Being sleepy is an excuse.

1936
01:43:22,500 --> 01:43:25,900
Alright. Let's check if it's cold outside.

1937
01:43:25,890 --> 01:43:28,520
His father is taking him outside.

1938
01:43:28,510 --> 01:43:32,710
It's fine. Come. Tell me if it's cold or not.

1939
01:43:32,700 --> 01:43:37,410
As your mom said you will become energetic from walking.

1940
01:43:37,400 --> 01:43:41,430
The dad's reasoning removed the excuse about being sleepy.

1941
01:43:41,420 --> 01:43:44,040
Look at this racket once more.

1942
01:43:44,220 --> 01:43:46,490
This means a lot to your mommy.

1943
01:43:46,480 --> 01:43:50,150
- Remember it, Yuu.
- I'm begging you.

1944
01:43:51,250 --> 01:43:51,950
What?

1945
01:43:51,940 --> 01:43:54,360
I want to go with mom.

1946
01:43:54,350 --> 01:44:00,150
"I want to go with mom". That's not an excuse.
He still struggles to find the willpower.

1947
01:44:00,140 --> 01:44:02,290
Let's send you off.

1948
01:44:03,360 --> 01:44:04,790
Can you go?

1949
01:44:04,780 --> 01:44:06,790
I can't go.

1950
01:44:06,780 --> 01:44:08,330
Really?

1951
01:44:08,750 --> 01:44:11,910
They must seize this moment.

1952
01:44:11,900 --> 01:44:15,340
Exactly. Find that energy.

1953
01:44:15,400 --> 01:44:17,300
He has lots of power.

1954
01:44:17,290 --> 01:44:20,070
I want to keep crying.

1955
01:44:20,060 --> 01:44:22,210
Harvesting the energy from crying.

1956
01:44:22,200 --> 01:44:25,850
Alright. Try to cry with all your might.

1957
01:44:26,030 --> 01:44:32,890
Here is a mother who is experienced with tears having to appear before finding the willpower.

1958
01:44:32,880 --> 01:44:36,170
The mother is just smiling through it.

1959
01:44:34,560 --> 01:44:41,760
If you have to cry then cry but
turn that energy into something

1960
01:44:41,750 --> 01:44:45,300
and do something with it. That is crucial.

1961
01:44:45,490 --> 01:44:50,220
Of course, Ai knows all about finding the willpower.

1962
01:44:51,270 --> 01:44:53,360
Tell me what you dislike about it.

1963
01:44:53,350 --> 01:44:55,490
I will become a missing child.

1964
01:44:55,480 --> 01:45:00,590
You will definitely not. Follow the road straight ahead. You don't have to turn even once.

1965
01:45:00,580 --> 01:45:01,810
Just has to go straight.

1966
01:45:01,800 --> 01:45:03,350
It's simple.

1967
01:45:03,920 --> 01:45:08,530
When someone yawns then it means that they are sleepy.

1968
01:45:08,520 --> 01:45:11,740
That's just an excuse.

1969
01:45:11,730 --> 01:45:14,380
I get it. When you are nervous you yawn.

1970
01:45:14,380 --> 01:45:16,290
She thwarted yet another excuse.

1971
01:45:16,280 --> 01:45:19,450
What if I become lonely.

1972
01:45:19,440 --> 01:45:21,070
This is reality.

1973
01:45:21,060 --> 01:45:25,300
I get it. I have prepared something
so you won't get lonely.

1974
01:45:25,290 --> 01:45:29,370
They've even thought of a way to avoid him from getting lonely.

1975
01:45:29,370 --> 01:45:33,380
A teddy bear. His name is Daiji (precious).

1976
01:45:33,370 --> 01:45:40,930
As a baby he would wrap it in a towel
and never ever let it out of his sight.

1977
01:45:40,920 --> 01:45:44,550
Mommy will be in trouble without the racket.

1978
01:45:44,540 --> 01:45:47,410
He tries to avoid going by taking Daiji out.

1979
01:45:47,400 --> 01:45:50,200
Then it can't be helped.
Let's cancel the party.

1980
01:45:50,190 --> 01:45:53,140
His mothers final measure.

1981
01:45:53,250 --> 01:45:56,500
It's fine. If you can't do it then fine.

1982
01:45:56,490 --> 01:46:00,850
Meanwhile, his father is in the parking lot.

1983
01:46:00,840 --> 01:46:03,400
- He's not witnessing any of this.
- That's right.

1984
01:46:03,390 --> 01:46:06,800
Will he go? I want him to but...

1985
01:46:06,790 --> 01:46:09,970
His father also can't find the resolution.

1986
01:46:08,520 --> 01:46:11,970
He's close to letting him give up.

1987
01:46:09,960 --> 01:46:14,410
I will refuse in front of everyone.
I will tell them that Yuu can't do it.

1988
01:46:14,400 --> 01:46:17,100
His mother is resolute that he has to go.

1989
01:46:17,320 --> 01:46:18,930
No way.

1990
01:46:18,920 --> 01:46:19,830
No way, right?

1991
01:46:19,820 --> 01:46:25,270
And at that moment Yuu's crying changes.

1992
01:46:25,490 --> 01:46:27,030
I will go get it.

1993
01:46:27,020 --> 01:46:29,230
Will you? Thank you.

1994
01:46:29,220 --> 01:46:31,990
Will we meet again when I come back?

1995
01:46:31,980 --> 01:46:35,380
Of course. That's a given.

1996
01:46:35,810 --> 01:46:39,530
Hug me for 5 minutes and then I will go.

1997
01:46:39,520 --> 01:46:40,800
Okay.

1998
01:46:41,150 --> 01:46:45,690
Something took hold in Yuu's heart.

1999
01:46:45,680 --> 01:46:56,180
I will hug you for 5 minutes so you can gather your strength and decide to go.

2000
01:46:56,170 --> 01:47:00,090
Yuu, you are mammas child so you can definitely do it.

2001
01:47:00,520 --> 01:47:03,170
Tell me when you feel strong enough to go.

2002
01:47:03,160 --> 01:47:05,220
And then wait. (Rule 3)

2003
01:47:05,210 --> 01:47:08,130
Tell me when you are ready.

2004
01:47:09,400 --> 01:47:10,550
Can you go?

2005
01:47:11,810 --> 01:47:13,400
He found the willpower.

2006
01:47:13,390 --> 01:47:15,560
I will go.

2007
01:47:15,350 --> 01:47:16,660
Remarkable.

2008
01:47:16,650 --> 01:47:22,420
Alright. Let's do our best.
If it's you, Yuu, then you can do it.

2009
01:47:22,410 --> 01:47:25,250
Take mama's...

2010
01:47:24,520 --> 01:47:29,040
Can do it.

2011
01:47:25,240 --> 01:47:29,590
The good luck charm contains his mothers wish.

2012
01:47:29,580 --> 01:47:32,740
This is a special backpack.

2013
01:47:32,730 --> 01:47:34,150
This is for rackets.

2014
01:47:34,140 --> 01:47:35,920
Rackets can fit in it.

2015
01:47:35,910 --> 01:47:39,140
Papa attached this special band to it.

2016
01:47:39,130 --> 01:47:48,040
The father thought of this and created it.
There's a hole at the bottom that the grip can go through.

2017
01:47:48,030 --> 01:47:51,350
Will he be able to explain this to the cake maker?

2018
01:47:51,340 --> 01:47:59,490
Alright. Ready to go.
Please do it. Thank you.

2019
01:47:59,480 --> 01:48:02,370
Can you go from here or should I follow you to the road?

2020
01:48:04,150 --> 01:48:07,020
If it's Yuu, then I can do it.

2021
01:48:05,820 --> 01:48:07,830
Amazing.

2022
01:48:07,070 --> 01:48:08,870
Off you go then.

2023
01:48:08,270 --> 01:48:09,830
He suddenly changed.

2024
01:48:09,180 --> 01:48:15,360
He's gathered all this energy from crying
it's almost like he's a different person.

2025
01:48:15,350 --> 01:48:17,300
Alright, I can do it.

2026
01:48:16,760 --> 01:48:18,840
You can do it.

2027
01:48:18,240 --> 01:48:21,540
It's straight forward and downhill.

2028
01:48:21,530 --> 01:48:24,560
He needs to pick up the racket from the cake shop.

2029
01:48:24,550 --> 01:48:37,330
At the convenience store he was asked to get 2 packs of three-color rice balls as well as a cherry blossom steamed bun.

2030
01:48:38,220 --> 01:48:41,990
Yuu likes to be seen by people and held in esteem.

2031
01:48:41,980 --> 01:48:48,630
But today he is all alone which is hard for him.

2032
01:48:48,620 --> 01:48:56,120
At this moment someone who is always watching Yuu, believes that he can accomplish this.

2033
01:48:56,490 --> 01:48:57,960
- Amazing.
- What is?

2034
01:48:57,950 --> 01:49:00,600
I could never do this errand.

2035
01:49:00,590 --> 01:49:03,320
- Of course you could.
- I see but...

2036
01:49:03,310 --> 01:49:08,830
- Whose kid do you think it is? It's my kid.
- Hey, make some room for me.

2037
01:49:08,820 --> 01:49:13,970
Did he feel their confidence in him?
Yuu started running.

2038
01:49:13,960 --> 01:49:17,750
Right, heading towards the cake shop.

2039
01:49:17,740 --> 01:49:25,880
Erm wait!? There's a convenience store on the way there? Actually there are 3 right around here.

2040
01:49:25,870 --> 01:49:33,360
The blossom viewing party basket is in the 100 yen convenience store not here.

2041
01:49:33,350 --> 01:49:41,700
The things he was asked to get
I bet they aren't here.

2042
01:49:45,000 --> 01:49:47,250
A pink steamed bun as requested?

2043
01:49:47,240 --> 01:49:49,780
Found it.

2044
01:49:47,240 --> 01:49:49,780
Found it?

2045
01:49:49,770 --> 01:49:54,280
It's a thank you "Heisei era for being over" bun.

2046
01:49:52,700 --> 01:49:54,280
Not it.

2047
01:49:54,270 --> 01:49:57,840
No three-colored rice balls
but he picked up mitarashi rice balls.

2048
01:50:00,400 --> 01:50:01,960
Please and thanks.

2049
01:50:01,950 --> 01:50:05,090
Unfortunately both of them are off.

2050
01:50:04,110 --> 01:50:06,800
They are close enough.

2051
01:50:07,320 --> 01:50:09,820
Today it's a cherry blossom viewing party.

2052
01:50:09,810 --> 01:50:12,230
His first conversation on the errand.

2053
01:50:12,220 --> 01:50:15,990
Because of the party I had to come alone today.

2054
01:50:13,560 --> 01:50:15,990
Amazing, he can converse.

2055
01:50:15,980 --> 01:50:17,320
That's the spirit.

2056
01:50:17,310 --> 01:50:21,330
It's my first time coming out like this alone.

2057
01:50:21,770 --> 01:50:23,250
Properly paying.

2058
01:50:23,240 --> 01:50:25,000
From 1000 yen.

2059
01:50:29,370 --> 01:50:32,230
And getting the money back.

2060
01:50:34,380 --> 01:50:38,390
He was living in Chigasaki prefecture and he's coming home today

2061
01:50:38,380 --> 01:50:39,200
He is?

2062
01:50:39,190 --> 01:50:40,170
back to Japan.

2063
01:50:40,160 --> 01:50:42,130
That's the usual Yuu.

2064
01:50:42,120 --> 01:50:45,010
Chigasaki is in Japan, though.

2065
01:50:45,000 --> 01:50:49,810
Since I will become a young boy...

2066
01:50:49,800 --> 01:50:56,210
Yesterday was a kindergarten entrance ceremony​
and he's proud to be considered a young boy.

2067
01:50:58,820 --> 01:51:00,740
Can't forget this.

2068
01:51:00,730 --> 01:51:03,690
No good. He forgot just like his dad.

2069
01:51:03,950 --> 01:51:05,240
Thank you.

2070
01:51:06,640 --> 01:51:10,310
He bought the wrong things but he feels accomplished now.

2071
01:51:10,300 --> 01:51:13,880
He can do things even if people aren't watching.

2072
01:51:13,870 --> 01:51:16,960
Nah, they were watching.

2073
01:51:18,180 --> 01:51:19,850
Switch it up.

2074
01:51:21,240 --> 01:51:23,490
What are they doing?

2075
01:51:23,450 --> 01:51:26,360
Alright, let's split it.

2076
01:51:23,450 --> 01:51:26,360
They are sharing it!

2077
01:51:27,420 --> 01:51:29,370
What's up with this comedy duo.

2078
01:51:28,840 --> 01:51:30,690
From their expensive apartment.

2079
01:51:30,680 --> 01:51:32,040
I can see. Can you?

2080
01:51:32,030 --> 01:51:34,640
They are watching over him.

2081
01:51:32,730 --> 01:51:34,640
Such a good relation.

2082
01:51:34,860 --> 01:51:36,760
That was funny.

2083
01:51:39,390 --> 01:51:39,940
Peew.

2084
01:51:39,970 --> 01:51:42,420
He dropped something.

2085
01:51:42,040 --> 01:51:44,420
Oh no, Daiji.

2086
01:51:45,200 --> 01:51:48,690
It's Daiji (precious) the teddy bear.

2087
01:51:49,090 --> 01:51:55,750
He dropped Daiji and ran off and as an exception the staff called out to him about Daiji.

2088
01:51:51,180 --> 01:51:53,860
He didn't notice.

2089
01:51:56,950 --> 01:52:03,290
It's dangerous running so close to the road and you seem to have dropped something.

2090
01:52:03,280 --> 01:52:04,130
Huh?

2091
01:52:04,120 --> 01:52:06,310
Is that brown thing not yours?

2092
01:52:08,500 --> 01:52:10,110
Daiji isn't there.

2093
01:52:10,330 --> 01:52:12,010
It fell off from there.

2094
01:52:12,420 --> 01:52:17,490
Daiji was with him when he learned to walk and of course they always slept together.

2095
01:52:17,480 --> 01:52:22,910
And when he rides a car or when they went to France he can go anywhere as long as Daiji is with him.

2096
01:52:22,900 --> 01:52:27,330
This 6th generation Daiji who is a bit dirty.

2097
01:52:25,130 --> 01:52:28,050
- 6th generation.
- That much?

2098
01:52:29,020 --> 01:52:31,450
Never leave my side.

2099
01:52:30,790 --> 01:52:31,970
Alright.

2100
01:52:51,360 --> 01:52:56,200
He's exhausted from going down the hill. For those times...

2101
01:52:56,190 --> 01:52:58,740
Energy injection.

2102
01:52:58,730 --> 01:53:01,310
It's candy for revitalizing him.

2103
01:53:00,480 --> 01:53:01,310
Candy.

2104
01:53:01,300 --> 01:53:07,500
"Please eat it when you feel exhausted" his mother said and put it in his pocket.

2105
01:53:07,320 --> 01:53:09,100
He's walking again.

2106
01:53:09,090 --> 01:53:12,900
Yuu who came to a sudden stop started walking again.

2107
01:53:12,890 --> 01:53:14,900
Here I go.

2108
01:53:17,060 --> 01:53:19,010
It's the cake shop.

2109
01:53:19,000 --> 01:53:25,720
As part of the Swiss owned hotel
here they make their own original cakes.

2110
01:53:23,990 --> 01:53:25,720
Looks so yummy.

2111
01:53:25,710 --> 01:53:29,890
He came to pick up the racket his father forgot there.

2112
01:53:31,790 --> 01:53:33,490
Hello.

2113
01:53:33,480 --> 01:53:35,380
The owner and chef.

2114
01:53:35,370 --> 01:53:37,380
Please give me a racket.

2115
01:53:37,370 --> 01:53:38,840
A racket?

2116
01:53:39,040 --> 01:53:42,010
Mama used to play tennis.

2117
01:53:42,000 --> 01:53:45,820
Mama's racket? I will go look for it.

2118
01:53:45,970 --> 01:53:48,170
Must be inside the kitchen.

2119
01:53:48,160 --> 01:53:50,770
He was able to explain it.

2120
01:53:50,760 --> 01:53:55,140
The chef understood it too
that this is an important racket

2121
01:53:55,130 --> 01:53:56,870
Is this the one?

2122
01:53:56,860 --> 01:54:00,300
He's making sure that this is mamas racket.

2123
01:54:00,290 --> 01:54:04,660
Not like many people forget rackets in this place.

2124
01:54:04,650 --> 01:54:06,710
Please put it in this red bag for me.

2125
01:54:06,700 --> 01:54:10,600
Explaining this will be difficult.

2126
01:54:08,830 --> 01:54:10,320
This one.

2127
01:54:10,590 --> 01:54:12,750
This one? Will it fit?

2128
01:54:12,740 --> 01:54:13,890
It will.

2129
01:54:13,880 --> 01:54:15,380
It's bigger than the bag.

2130
01:54:15,370 --> 01:54:21,390
Not this end. From here.
There's a hole down here.

2131
01:54:17,790 --> 01:54:19,770
That's right.

2132
01:54:21,380 --> 01:54:23,240
Ah, there is a hole.

2133
01:54:21,840 --> 01:54:23,220
Amazing.

2134
01:54:23,230 --> 01:54:25,740
And put it through here.

2135
01:54:25,730 --> 01:54:29,520
He was able to explain it.

2136
01:54:27,940 --> 01:54:29,520
Amazing.

2137
01:54:29,510 --> 01:54:35,700
And then put it through here.

2138
01:54:35,690 --> 01:54:38,090
I am?

2139
01:54:35,690 --> 01:54:38,090
You're sweating.

2140
01:54:38,080 --> 01:54:41,780
Chef, we appreciate your help.

2141
01:54:40,600 --> 01:54:41,780
It's your fault.

2142
01:54:41,770 --> 01:54:43,590
Cause he's using all his effort.

2143
01:54:43,580 --> 01:54:47,880
The chef is using all his skill.

2144
01:54:45,760 --> 01:54:49,690
- Chef!
- Chef, thank you very much.

2145
01:54:50,290 --> 01:54:51,520
That's perfect.

2146
01:54:51,510 --> 01:54:52,780
That's right.

2147
01:54:52,770 --> 01:54:55,240
Wanna try it out?

2148
01:54:55,230 --> 01:54:56,790
Fits perfectly.

2149
01:54:56,780 --> 01:54:59,140
It is?

2150
01:54:56,780 --> 01:54:59,140
This is fine.

2151
01:54:59,130 --> 01:55:01,790
Alright, take it back to your mother.

2152
01:55:01,780 --> 01:55:08,670
Mothers important racket and the groceries.

2153
01:55:08,660 --> 01:55:10,030
Thank you.

2154
01:55:10,540 --> 01:55:12,810
Thank you very much, chef.

2155
01:55:14,760 --> 01:55:21,070
The 100 yen convinience store where the requested items are on the other side of the road.

2156
01:55:21,050 --> 01:55:24,820
It's very close to where he's walking right now.

2157
01:55:24,810 --> 01:55:27,440
I wonder if he got the racket.

2158
01:55:27,430 --> 01:55:30,770
They can't see well from this angle.

2159
01:55:30,760 --> 01:55:32,970
Can't see at all.

2160
01:55:34,110 --> 01:55:40,110
Even if no one is watching over him
Yuu is doing just fine, mother.

2161
01:55:41,540 --> 01:55:45,240
- He finally went out.
- He did.

2162
01:55:45,230 --> 01:55:50,200
- How has it been so far?
- It really took a while to get him to leave.

2163
01:55:50,190 --> 01:55:58,040
I was worried if he would be fine but gradually his behavior changed so I started having confidence in him.

2164
01:55:58,030 --> 01:55:59,620
It changed the moment he left.

2165
01:55:59,610 --> 01:56:02,460
Even I was surprised by that change.

2166
01:56:02,630 --> 01:56:08,160
Now I understand the strength of your son
but I also understood the weakness of your husband.

2167
01:56:08,150 --> 01:56:09,830
Yeah, the husband.

2168
01:56:09,820 --> 01:56:13,090
He was so anxious the day before.

2169
01:56:13,080 --> 01:56:16,940
Even he didn't understood why he was crying.

2170
01:56:16,930 --> 01:56:19,060
Even said that he couldn't do the errand.

2171
01:56:19,050 --> 01:56:24,650
About this teary-eyed father
he is in fact in the studio today

2172
01:56:24,640 --> 01:56:27,090
Yuu's papa, where are you?

2173
01:56:27,240 --> 01:56:29,010
Thank you very much.

2174
01:56:31,520 --> 01:56:37,320
Since you came all the way,
why don't you come and sit here with us?

2175
01:56:37,310 --> 01:56:39,380
Isn't that right, everybody?

2176
01:56:39,370 --> 01:56:40,580
Come and watch.

2177
01:56:40,570 --> 01:56:43,180
From "my first errand" to "my first trial".

2178
01:56:43,170 --> 01:56:45,080
The father is on trial now.

2179
01:56:45,070 --> 01:56:47,380
He's already crying.

2180
01:56:47,480 --> 01:56:50,660
Just finished wailing.

2181
01:56:50,660 --> 01:56:53,110
Papa, please share how you feel.

2182
01:56:53,100 --> 01:56:55,430
I can't find the words.

2183
01:56:55,420 --> 01:56:57,910
- Mama is so strong.
- She is.

2184
01:56:57,900 --> 01:57:05,440
Just like she said. If I was alone in this I would immediately give in and go with him to pick it up.

2185
01:57:05,430 --> 01:57:13,430
It was mostly cut out but I was in that car for long mumbling "isn't it enough already".

2186
01:57:13,420 --> 01:57:17,880
I kept thinking about giving up but
Ai said that this kid can definitely do it.

2187
01:57:17,870 --> 01:57:23,640
Her confidence in our son was so strong that it started rubbing off on me too.

2188
01:57:23,630 --> 01:57:26,990
- It's the strength of a mother.
- What a cool mom.

2189
01:57:27,650 --> 01:57:30,520
It's time to go shopping again.

2190
01:57:30,510 --> 01:57:37,990
He needs to get 2 packs of three-color rice balls as well as a cherry blossom steamed bun. Then back to the tennis club.

2191
01:57:37,980 --> 01:57:41,610
Since he doesn't have to hold the racket he can raise his hand.

2192
01:57:41,600 --> 01:57:44,930
The father really thought of everything.

2193
01:57:45,390 --> 01:57:47,520
Isn't the camera too close?

2194
01:57:47,510 --> 01:57:51,300
No, it's fine.

2195
01:57:47,840 --> 01:57:50,510
Camera

2196
01:57:56,030 --> 01:57:58,030
Oh no.

2197
01:57:58,640 --> 01:58:02,220
For those times...

2198
01:58:00,040 --> 01:58:01,600
Suspicious.

2199
01:58:01,590 --> 01:58:03,920
Too suspicious.

2200
01:58:03,910 --> 01:58:09,620
Weird. No one behaves like that.

2201
01:58:09,610 --> 01:58:16,710
"Why is he playing tennis here?"
he wonders but he didn't notice the camera.

2202
01:58:14,890 --> 01:58:16,710
Amazing.

2203
01:58:16,700 --> 01:58:18,230
At this moment.

2204
01:58:18,220 --> 01:58:20,430
Yuu, take care.

2205
01:58:20,420 --> 01:58:24,080
The chef was watching over him.

2206
01:58:24,070 --> 01:58:25,360
Bye bye.

2207
01:58:25,350 --> 01:58:30,380
As expected, he does best when people watch over him.

2208
01:58:35,520 --> 01:58:37,970
He has arrived at the 100 yen store.

2209
01:58:37,960 --> 01:58:44,630
The cherry blossom viewing party basket is right near the entrence.

2210
01:58:44,350 --> 01:58:46,550
Found it.

2211
01:58:46,740 --> 01:58:53,180
He found the rice balls and was asked to get two.

2212
01:58:53,170 --> 01:58:56,820
- Remarkable.
- He knows to get two.

2213
01:58:57,900 --> 01:59:02,700
That's right. Here's another one for Yuu to talk to.

2214
01:59:03,120 --> 01:59:05,240
296 yen, please.

2215
01:59:05,670 --> 01:59:12,120
We are having a party. Mama, Yuu and papa will eat this.

2216
01:59:13,970 --> 01:59:16,100
Is this an important racket?

2217
01:59:16,090 --> 01:59:19,650
This is the racket that accomplished the first place.

2218
01:59:18,510 --> 01:59:20,550
Amazing, isn't it?

2219
01:59:19,640 --> 01:59:23,740
My mom used to be a tennis player

2220
01:59:23,730 --> 01:59:26,410
back then she used this racket.

2221
01:59:26,400 --> 01:59:31,160
Of all people, this is Sugiyama Ai's racket.

2222
01:59:31,150 --> 01:59:34,410
What kind of player was your mother?
Was she a great player?

2223
01:59:34,400 --> 01:59:37,030
Yes, she lost to everyone.

2224
01:59:34,400 --> 01:59:45,940
TN: He mistakes the preposition.
Tiny mistake but results in the opposite meaning.

2225
01:59:38,680 --> 01:59:41,240
- He's pretty wrong.
- It's the other way around.

2226
01:59:41,420 --> 01:59:43,410
She would lose to everyone.

2227
01:59:43,400 --> 01:59:45,940
She didn't lose to anyone.

2228
01:59:46,350 --> 01:59:48,790
Don't forget like your father.

2229
01:59:48,800 --> 01:59:51,110
Don't forget this.

2230
01:59:52,650 --> 01:59:54,690
Looks heavy.

2231
01:59:52,650 --> 01:59:54,690
Thank you.

2232
01:59:54,680 --> 02:00:00,360
Ah, he's there. Isn't that Yuu?
It is. Have a look.

2233
02:00:00,350 --> 02:00:03,070
And he's carrying something.

2234
02:00:05,600 --> 02:00:08,240
- I can't see.
- I want to see. I beg of you.

2235
02:00:08,120 --> 02:00:09,860
He's begging.

2236
02:00:09,020 --> 02:00:12,980
- Alright, have a look.
- Are you sure?

2237
02:00:13,170 --> 02:00:16,050
What they can't see is his expression.

2238
02:00:16,040 --> 02:00:19,480
And of course they can't see what he bought either.

2239
02:00:19,470 --> 02:00:23,670
He accomplished everything he was asked to do.

2240
02:00:23,660 --> 02:00:26,060
He's entering the convenience store again.

2241
02:00:26,050 --> 02:00:28,970
He already has all he needs.

2242
02:00:28,960 --> 02:00:31,950
What is he going to purchase?

2243
02:00:32,830 --> 02:00:40,040
He picked up the racket and purchased all that's needed so why did he go into a third convenience store?

2244
02:00:40,030 --> 02:00:42,210
What is he getting?

2245
02:00:42,200 --> 02:00:44,350
He really loves stores.

2246
02:00:43,730 --> 02:00:45,330
That's enough.

2247
02:00:48,590 --> 02:00:50,490
You can't carry all that, Yuu.

2248
02:00:51,120 --> 02:00:54,850
They could see he was carrying a lot.

2249
02:00:57,590 --> 02:01:00,810
There are no needed items.

2250
02:01:02,010 --> 02:01:04,240
Just come home.

2251
02:01:05,820 --> 02:01:09,090
There's nothing more to get.

2252
02:01:09,080 --> 02:01:11,140
What will he purchase?

2253
02:01:11,130 --> 02:01:13,990
Where is Pamu?

2254
02:01:13,980 --> 02:01:16,920
Pamu is the name of the tennis club.

2255
02:01:16,910 --> 02:01:20,180
Go back to Pamu?

2256
02:01:16,910 --> 02:01:20,180
I just want to go back to Pamu.

2257
02:01:21,160 --> 02:01:27,110
I want to go back there since I was running an errand and now I want to return.

2258
02:01:27,100 --> 02:01:31,850
Pamu isn't the name of a house so what is it?

2259
02:01:31,840 --> 02:01:35,080
In a court you go like this.

2260
02:01:35,610 --> 02:01:37,940
A tennis court?

2261
02:01:35,610 --> 02:01:37,940
That's right.

2262
02:01:37,930 --> 02:01:42,930
You would have to go up the hill.
Can you go up there?

2263
02:01:42,920 --> 02:01:44,590
I can do it.

2264
02:01:42,920 --> 02:01:44,590
You can?

2265
02:01:46,420 --> 02:01:49,360
Thank you.

2266
02:01:46,420 --> 02:01:49,360
Then please do your best.

2267
02:01:48,530 --> 02:01:49,360
Splendid.

2268
02:01:49,350 --> 02:01:54,140
He knew the way, of course.
He just wanted to talk.

2269
02:01:53,480 --> 02:01:55,210
I see.

2270
02:01:55,200 --> 02:01:58,110
Alright. I will go.

2271
02:02:20,170 --> 02:02:24,030
His resolute expression is different from his crying face.

2272
02:02:24,020 --> 02:02:28,220
But this power was born from his crying.

2273
02:02:28,730 --> 02:02:32,380
Mama must be waiting.

2274
02:02:34,330 --> 02:02:39,530
Mama's world No. 1 has been entrusted to Yuu.

2275
02:02:39,520 --> 02:02:41,650
This is so heavy.

2276
02:02:46,200 --> 02:02:49,750
Yuu is back at the tennis club.

2277
02:02:52,830 --> 02:02:53,870
Yuu!

2278
02:02:53,860 --> 02:02:57,170
How amazing.

2279
02:02:53,860 --> 02:02:57,170
I purchased this.

2280
02:02:57,160 --> 02:03:03,850
What did you buy? And my racket?
Thank you, it's my important racket.

2281
02:03:03,840 --> 02:03:08,050
- It's perfect.
- Amazing. Thank you.

2282
02:03:08,050 --> 02:03:10,550
You did a great job.

2283
02:03:10,780 --> 02:03:14,630
Did you manage to ask for it?

2284
02:03:14,620 --> 02:03:17,890
- At the cake shop?
- Did you ask the cake maker?

2285
02:03:17,880 --> 02:03:23,480
From happiness since you did so well. I think you are amazing.

2286
02:03:17,880 --> 02:03:23,480
Why are there tears coming out?

2287
02:03:24,410 --> 02:03:26,050
Where's the cake?

2288
02:03:26,690 --> 02:03:32,010
- First show us what you bought.
- Tell us, tell us.

2289
02:03:32,010 --> 02:03:34,140
The chef gave me...

2290
02:03:34,130 --> 02:03:38,370
Ah, mama loves those.

2291
02:03:34,130 --> 02:03:38,370
These things.

2292
02:03:38,360 --> 02:03:45,180
That's right mama. I thought mama loves these so...

2293
02:03:45,170 --> 02:03:48,410
That's right. I love mitarashi rice balls.

2294
02:03:48,400 --> 02:03:49,520
Amazing.

2295
02:03:49,510 --> 02:03:53,940
It was fun on my first errand.

2296
02:03:53,930 --> 02:03:58,090
He was happy to do it in the end.

2297
02:03:58,080 --> 02:04:00,700
Please eat this.

2298
02:04:00,840 --> 02:04:04,850
Time for the cherry blossom viewing party.

2299
02:04:03,830 --> 02:04:04,820
Wonderful.

2300
02:04:04,840 --> 02:04:09,920
Yuu did his best for the party. Thank you.

2301
02:04:10,540 --> 02:04:12,010
Did his best.

2302
02:04:13,740 --> 02:04:15,900
Nice smile.

2303
02:04:15,090 --> 02:04:16,260
Thank you, Yuu.

2304
02:04:16,250 --> 02:04:21,800
He was asked to get them but these are mama's beloved mitarashi rice balls.

2305
02:04:21,960 --> 02:04:23,740
Not that good.

2306
02:04:23,580 --> 02:04:25,400
Not that good?

2307
02:04:24,750 --> 02:04:26,170
Super tasty.

2308
02:04:27,360 --> 02:04:31,570
Everyone, be careful that it doesn't get caught in your throats

2309
02:04:31,560 --> 02:04:34,440
so please eat it slowly

2310
02:04:34,150 --> 02:04:36,020
He's worried about them.

2311
02:04:36,360 --> 02:04:39,890
Hey Yuu, what do you want to be when you grow up?

2312
02:04:40,470 --> 02:04:41,970
Cuisine.

2313
02:04:42,580 --> 02:04:43,690
Chef?

2314
02:04:44,670 --> 02:04:47,560
Neither golf nor tennis

2315
02:04:47,550 --> 02:04:52,020
but Yuu might become the worlds best chef.

2316
02:04:57,300 --> 02:04:59,160
- Splendid.
- It was splendid.

2317
02:04:59,150 --> 02:05:01,250
Got them because mama loves them.

2318
02:05:01,240 --> 02:05:03,210
That tugged at my heartstrings.

2319
02:05:03,200 --> 02:05:11,190
Yeah, at first I thought that we should get rice balls matching the color of cherry blossom

2320
02:05:11,180 --> 02:05:18,640
but normally I go for mitarashi rice balls and usually go for them so he must've been observing me.

2321
02:05:18,630 --> 02:05:21,250
- I totally thought he had made a mistake.
- That's right.

2322
02:05:21,240 --> 02:05:24,400
but it was to show gratitude towards his mother.

2323
02:05:24,390 --> 02:05:27,220
Father, are you okay after watching this?

2324
02:05:24,580 --> 02:05:27,080
Too much crying.

2325
02:05:27,210 --> 02:05:31,210
Well... I'm lost for words.

2326
02:05:31,200 --> 02:05:33,110
- Are you okay?
- Definitely not.

2327
02:05:33,100 --> 02:05:35,520
You were crying throughout.

2328
02:05:35,510 --> 02:05:41,330
And one staff member had a camera in his racket. What was all that about?

2329
02:05:41,320 --> 02:05:44,870
Who holds a racket like this?

2330
02:05:44,860 --> 02:05:54,140
What a cute kid. And just like how we watched a mother raising their boy this time we have a 4 year old girl.

2331
02:05:54,850 --> 02:06:02,370
Inami in Toyama prefecture is a
flourishing town built around a shrine.

2332
02:06:02,360 --> 02:06:11,370
Wood crafting is famous there and many sculptures around.

2333
02:06:08,480 --> 02:06:10,900
Amazing.

2334
02:06:11,360 --> 02:06:15,040
And there we find a bustling road leading up to the shrine.

2335
02:06:15,030 --> 02:06:18,850
At this kimono fabrics store we find a 4 year old girl.

2336
02:06:19,000 --> 02:06:22,040
Here is Sae who helps out her mother.

2337
02:06:20,780 --> 02:06:22,040
Admirable.

2338
02:06:22,030 --> 02:06:24,630
She does everything in earnestness.

2339
02:06:24,620 --> 02:06:30,030
She loves working at the shop and
she also helps out her grandmother.

2340
02:06:30,020 --> 02:06:38,040
Readying the spare change. Grandma brings them every day this to a supermarket close by.

2341
02:06:38,030 --> 02:06:40,610
Putting the change in a bag.

2342
02:06:40,970 --> 02:06:44,630
Off you go.

2343
02:06:40,970 --> 02:06:44,630
Taking off.

2344
02:06:44,620 --> 02:06:47,860
Mother.

2345
02:06:44,900 --> 02:06:48,910
Make sure to work hard and come back.

2346
02:06:49,410 --> 02:06:52,950
Grandma has been out for 20 minutes.

2347
02:06:52,940 --> 02:06:54,130
Yes, yes.

2348
02:06:54,120 --> 02:06:55,000
A call from her.

2349
02:06:54,990 --> 02:06:58,990
Ah Sae, she's saying that she forgot the money.

2350
02:06:58,980 --> 02:07:01,330
The 50 yen coin bag.

2351
02:07:01,320 --> 02:07:02,200
What?

2352
02:07:02,190 --> 02:07:04,570
The grandmas strategy.

2353
02:07:04,560 --> 02:07:06,920
What? Okay.

2354
02:07:06,970 --> 02:07:08,820
Found it!

2355
02:07:08,810 --> 02:07:10,530
They hid it.

2356
02:07:09,780 --> 02:07:10,970
I found it.

2357
02:07:10,960 --> 02:07:13,000
Sae is full of energy.

2358
02:07:12,990 --> 02:07:14,490
What should we do, Sae?

2359
02:07:14,480 --> 02:07:17,460
Does this mean that she will go on an errand?

2360
02:07:17,670 --> 02:07:19,780
Was it underneath it??

2361
02:07:19,780 --> 02:07:24,290
Sae, can you bring this? To Asamo.

2362
02:07:24,280 --> 02:07:25,700
Got it.

2363
02:07:24,280 --> 02:07:25,700
You did?

2364
02:07:25,690 --> 02:07:27,530
Alright.

2365
02:07:27,520 --> 02:07:33,370
The flowers for Buddha have withered. Can you also get some fresh ones?

2366
02:07:33,360 --> 02:07:34,450
Yes.

2367
02:07:34,440 --> 02:07:40,850
The town next door is after the big crossing
grandma's shop is in the supermarket

2368
02:07:40,840 --> 02:07:44,630
she can buy the flowers in the same building.

2369
02:07:44,620 --> 02:07:49,340
Off I go.

2370
02:07:44,620 --> 02:07:49,340
Take care. Take your time.

2371
02:07:49,330 --> 02:07:53,650
Sae, has been begging to go on
an errand so it can't be helped.

2372
02:07:53,640 --> 02:07:56,520
It's my first time.

2373
02:07:53,640 --> 02:07:56,520
TN: Ending a sentence in dawa is very lady like and cute.

2374
02:07:56,510 --> 02:07:58,190
So fun.

2375
02:07:57,450 --> 02:07:59,080
So fun.

2376
02:07:58,180 --> 02:08:04,440
This is her first errand and it's spring.

2377
02:08:09,220 --> 02:08:15,950
She has arrived at the crossing and this sculpture has been made in Inami.

2378
02:08:15,940 --> 02:08:19,070
Welcome to Inami.

2379
02:08:19,060 --> 02:08:21,480
It can talk.

2380
02:08:21,470 --> 02:08:24,540
From here on the scenery immediately changes.

2381
02:08:24,530 --> 02:08:30,550
A wide crossing with no obstructed view
and since few cars pass there are no traffic lights.

2382
02:08:30,540 --> 02:08:33,040
She always crosses with her grandmother.

2383
02:08:33,030 --> 02:08:41,270
Right, left, right.

2384
02:08:41,260 --> 02:08:48,600
Sae never looked back once.
She looks and walks forward.

2385
02:08:48,970 --> 02:08:51,010
Ah, she crossed.

2386
02:08:58,620 --> 02:09:00,600
She crossed it.

2387
02:09:02,270 --> 02:09:04,910
It's hot.

2388
02:09:04,900 --> 02:09:08,960
Sae broke a good sweat.

2389
02:09:08,950 --> 02:09:18,490
She has a towel in her right for wiping her sweat
in her left pocket she has a towel for tears.

2390
02:09:18,480 --> 02:09:22,630
What are the carving today?
A dragon or a daruma?

2391
02:09:22,620 --> 02:09:27,460
She considered asking them
but she can't today.

2392
02:09:27,450 --> 02:09:37,410
I have to go to Asumo I can't do other things.

2393
02:09:37,400 --> 02:09:40,840
The pink roof is where she is headed.

2394
02:09:40,830 --> 02:09:44,760
I finally approached it.

2395
02:09:45,620 --> 02:09:50,040
Just like mother said, if you go
straight then it's right there.

2396
02:09:50,450 --> 02:09:56,180
I can go by myself. How great. I'm a genius.

2397
02:09:56,170 --> 02:09:58,180
A genius.

2398
02:10:00,320 --> 02:10:04,200
Ah, it's cool. Always great with air condition.

2399
02:10:05,520 --> 02:10:07,600
This is her grandmothers shop.

2400
02:10:07,590 --> 02:10:12,980
Grandma, I brought you the things you forgot.

2401
02:10:12,970 --> 02:10:15,800
She gave it her all just for her grandmother.

2402
02:10:15,790 --> 02:10:18,410
It was beneath the pillow.

2403
02:10:18,400 --> 02:10:20,830
Thank you so much. I was in trouble.

2404
02:10:20,820 --> 02:10:23,560
Grandma, please don't forget.

2405
02:10:23,550 --> 02:10:28,200
Now it's all there. Thank you for bringing it here.

2406
02:10:28,240 --> 02:10:31,020
I will get flowers too.

2407
02:10:28,240 --> 02:10:31,020
Please do.

2408
02:10:31,010 --> 02:10:34,790
In fact, a monk will come visit grandpa house.

2409
02:10:34,780 --> 02:10:37,290
Hello.

2410
02:10:37,280 --> 02:10:39,580
I came by myself.

2411
02:10:39,570 --> 02:10:46,100
Uwa, so many beatiful flowers.
I'm completely at loss.

2412
02:10:46,090 --> 02:10:53,520
Flowers for buddha, they are all made to be similar but it seems like she's found the best one.

2413
02:10:53,510 --> 02:10:55,520
These are cute.

2414
02:10:55,900 --> 02:10:58,680
Flowers for buddha, I will go home with these.

2415
02:10:58,670 --> 02:11:02,130
You dropped your wallet.

2416
02:11:02,120 --> 02:11:04,820
Her important purse given to her by grandma.

2417
02:11:04,810 --> 02:11:07,860
380 yen please.

2418
02:11:08,300 --> 02:11:11,340
She has two 500 yen coins in her wallet.

2419
02:11:11,430 --> 02:11:15,200
Since I'm just a kid I don't know if this is enough.

2420
02:11:15,840 --> 02:11:18,720
Just one 500 yen coin please.

2421
02:11:18,710 --> 02:11:23,280
She always handles the loose change
but today is her first time paying.

2422
02:11:23,270 --> 02:11:28,620
Here you go. Thank you.

2423
02:11:23,270 --> 02:11:28,620
Thank you.

2424
02:11:31,740 --> 02:11:35,410
Ah, it was cool inside.

2425
02:11:36,560 --> 02:11:41,720
It's April and the Hokuriku regions' summer has begun.

2426
02:11:40,560 --> 02:11:43,750
That's right.

2427
02:11:44,770 --> 02:11:48,160
It's become hotter than before.

2428
02:11:54,860 --> 02:11:58,220
Clank clank clank sounds can be heard.

2429
02:11:58,210 --> 02:12:00,400
She's almost home.

2430
02:12:00,390 --> 02:12:02,920
Hot today.

2431
02:12:00,390 --> 02:12:02,920
Yep.

2432
02:12:04,670 --> 02:12:10,280
Everyone watches over her
and that's why she can do her best.

2433
02:12:10,270 --> 02:12:14,260
This town raises and holds children dear.

2434
02:12:14,250 --> 02:12:19,070
That's been going on for years
and is now part of normal life in Inami.

2435
02:12:20,810 --> 02:12:23,220
I'm home.

2436
02:12:23,480 --> 02:12:24,880
Welcome home.

2437
02:12:24,870 --> 02:12:26,500
I was able to do it.

2438
02:12:26,740 --> 02:12:28,580
I was able to go by myself.

2439
02:12:28,570 --> 02:12:30,890
Really? You are remarkable.

2440
02:12:30,400 --> 02:12:32,200
Splendid.

2441
02:12:32,250 --> 02:12:37,140
On my way back it was way hotter than the way over there.

2442
02:12:37,130 --> 02:12:38,860
She's sweating a lot.

2443
02:12:38,070 --> 02:12:38,850
Was it fun?

2444
02:12:38,840 --> 02:12:40,450
It was fun.

2445
02:12:40,470 --> 02:12:42,710
So it was fun.

2446
02:12:43,050 --> 02:12:47,770
Which is why the mother conceived a second errand.

2447
02:12:47,760 --> 02:12:58,050
She will go visit the temple to call the monk over to their home so that she can pray at their home altar.

2448
02:12:58,040 --> 02:13:05,110
There are many temples in Inami so her mother is trying to give her clear directions.

2449
02:13:05,100 --> 02:13:14,140
If you go this way, on the right side there is a spinning blue and red thing, right?

2450
02:13:14,160 --> 02:13:17,960
It's a spinning barber's pole.

2451
02:13:18,010 --> 02:13:21,380
With it to your back you will have the temple in front of you.

2452
02:13:22,320 --> 02:13:23,890
Butsugon temple.

2453
02:13:24,550 --> 02:13:27,590
It is. You understand?

2454
02:13:24,550 --> 02:13:27,590
Oh, that one?

2455
02:13:28,050 --> 02:13:30,100
Alright. Got it.

2456
02:13:30,090 --> 02:13:33,860
Good, good, good, good, gooooood.

2457
02:13:31,210 --> 02:13:33,390
Nice smile.

2458
02:13:34,630 --> 02:13:36,150
I will head off.

2459
02:13:36,140 --> 02:13:41,040
My life is so full of errands.

2460
02:13:58,000 --> 02:14:02,710
My life is so full of errands.

2461
02:14:02,150 --> 02:14:03,980
What's up with this song.

2462
02:14:03,340 --> 02:14:11,560
This isn't her first errand, it's her second.
She's looking for the spinning barber's pole.

2463
02:14:11,550 --> 02:14:18,040
Spinning spinning, where are you? Spinning.

2464
02:14:18,510 --> 02:14:24,230
Ah, it's there. Seems like it's their day off.

2465
02:14:25,020 --> 02:14:26,260
She passed it by.

2466
02:14:25,690 --> 02:14:28,130
Was hard to see.

2467
02:14:28,120 --> 02:14:31,960
And that's right this is the temple.

2468
02:14:32,870 --> 02:14:36,370
The cameraman races ahead of her.

2469
02:14:36,760 --> 02:14:38,410
Wait, she stopped.

2470
02:14:41,360 --> 02:14:43,270
She turned back.

2471
02:14:45,120 --> 02:14:55,810
That's odd. Her mother mentioned this spinning pole but it's quite inconspicuous.

2472
02:14:55,810 --> 02:15:00,050
Why can't this errand veteran see it?

2473
02:15:00,060 --> 02:15:04,300
Mother, it wasn't spinning at all.

2474
02:15:05,550 --> 02:15:08,530
Even if it isn't spinning that's the right one.

2475
02:15:08,550 --> 02:15:10,960
I stood with it to my back.

2476
02:15:10,950 --> 02:15:12,290
Was there a temple?

2477
02:15:12,280 --> 02:15:19,540
There was but there are temples here and there so I wouldn't know.

2478
02:15:19,530 --> 02:15:21,700
She really gave it her all.

2479
02:15:20,730 --> 02:15:23,190
Cause that's what kind of town it is.

2480
02:15:23,180 --> 02:15:24,630
I will tell you.

2481
02:15:24,620 --> 02:15:28,820
I will put this on you.

2482
02:15:28,840 --> 02:15:32,450
She put a glittering bracelet on her right hand.

2483
02:15:32,730 --> 02:15:35,250
Do this and it's the temple on the left.

2484
02:15:35,240 --> 02:15:37,310
To the right of the spinning pole.

2485
02:15:37,300 --> 02:15:39,810
Do you understand?

2486
02:15:37,300 --> 02:15:39,810
I understand.

2487
02:15:39,800 --> 02:15:43,530
Did you see it though it wasn't spinning?

2488
02:15:43,520 --> 02:15:45,970
It wasn't spinning.

2489
02:15:45,960 --> 02:15:50,890
I thought it would but it's their day off today. I'm sorry.

2490
02:15:50,880 --> 02:15:53,700
Mother, you were slightly bad.

2491
02:15:54,200 --> 02:15:55,280
That's right.

2492
02:15:55,280 --> 02:15:58,010
This errands veteran is ready to departure.

2493
02:15:58,000 --> 02:16:01,950
Okay, I've understood.

2494
02:15:58,000 --> 02:16:01,950
Say "excuse me" in a loud voice.

2495
02:16:02,440 --> 02:16:04,630
I'm fine.

2496
02:16:02,440 --> 02:16:04,630
You will fall if you run.

2497
02:16:10,300 --> 02:16:19,750
She can do it if she understands what. That's Sae's good point. But she is getting tired. This is her second errand today after all.

2498
02:16:18,770 --> 02:16:19,750
And it's hot.

2499
02:16:20,330 --> 02:16:23,060
Alright, she has arrived in front of the pole.

2500
02:16:24,730 --> 02:16:26,850
It's fine even if it doesn't spin.

2501
02:16:27,210 --> 02:16:34,180
With it to your back there is a temple on the right and one on the left. Which one is it?

2502
02:16:31,140 --> 02:16:33,810
- So that's what it was.
- That's hard to discern.

2503
02:16:34,280 --> 02:16:38,270
According to the bracelet that her mother put on her.

2504
02:16:39,930 --> 02:16:41,110
This one?

2505
02:16:41,100 --> 02:16:47,100
That's right. The temple on the right. The Butsugon temple.

2506
02:16:46,560 --> 02:16:48,680
Glad she got it.

2507
02:16:49,460 --> 02:16:53,250
This is her first time alone at a temple.

2508
02:16:51,740 --> 02:16:55,710
- Scary to be alone at a temple.
- It is scary.

2509
02:16:56,740 --> 02:16:59,430
Straight to the main building.

2510
02:17:01,630 --> 02:17:08,330
One step at a time. The talkative Sae is really quiet right now.

2511
02:17:12,560 --> 02:17:14,370
Excuse me.

2512
02:17:14,360 --> 02:17:17,800
She calls out with a loud voice.

2513
02:17:21,200 --> 02:17:23,420
No one comes out.

2514
02:17:24,290 --> 02:17:27,410
She won't cry. She won't be perturbed.

2515
02:17:27,450 --> 02:17:28,970
Excuse me.

2516
02:17:29,090 --> 02:17:33,050
She calls out in an even louder voice this time.

2517
02:17:33,310 --> 02:17:37,590
But no one comes out.

2518
02:17:35,260 --> 02:17:37,330
Why not?

2519
02:17:43,950 --> 02:17:47,400
There's also a building over there.

2520
02:17:47,900 --> 02:17:53,560
That's right. This is the building where the monk lives which is also called Kuri.

2521
02:17:53,550 --> 02:17:55,480
The door is open.

2522
02:17:55,470 --> 02:18:02,760
If she goes inside and calls out loudly then the monk will come out but she doesn't go in.

2523
02:18:02,750 --> 02:18:06,680
She can't bring herself forward.

2524
02:18:06,880 --> 02:18:10,520
It's dark inside and smells heavily of incense.

2525
02:18:13,430 --> 02:18:17,930
Since this is the way she better
fight through the scary feeling.

2526
02:18:17,920 --> 02:18:23,530
The bracelet her mother gave her is her only support.

2527
02:18:23,520 --> 02:18:26,970
Alright, I will head in. At that moment...

2528
02:18:31,410 --> 02:18:35,300
Alright, I will head in. At that moment...

2529
02:18:39,690 --> 02:18:43,250
The bracelet broke.

2530
02:18:44,860 --> 02:18:50,600
She picks up the beads but she can't fix it.

2531
02:18:54,680 --> 02:18:57,960
Sae, is this all too much?

2532
02:19:00,620 --> 02:19:08,440
She won't go home. These are all new
experiences for the 4 year old Sae.

2533
02:19:08,430 --> 02:19:11,010
And then this expression.

2534
02:19:23,120 --> 02:19:25,060
Excuse me.

2535
02:19:27,650 --> 02:19:29,460
Excuse me.

2536
02:19:29,500 --> 02:19:31,010
Yes.

2537
02:19:30,940 --> 02:19:32,740
Thankfully.

2538
02:19:35,560 --> 02:19:36,910
Who's there?

2539
02:19:36,900 --> 02:19:40,010
From within the dark someone approaches.

2540
02:19:40,000 --> 02:19:41,640
Isn't this Sae?

2541
02:19:41,630 --> 02:19:42,290
Yes.

2542
02:19:42,280 --> 02:19:45,130
But it's a familiar face.

2543
02:19:47,080 --> 02:19:48,490
This is the monk.

2544
02:19:48,480 --> 02:19:51,240
Please sit down.

2545
02:19:51,230 --> 02:19:52,610
What's wrong?

2546
02:19:52,600 --> 02:19:54,480
Here.

2547
02:19:52,600 --> 02:19:54,480
I will receive this.

2548
02:19:54,470 --> 02:19:56,520
It's a gift for Buddha.

2549
02:19:58,730 --> 02:20:05,000
I called you but you were a bit slow so I was wandering around.

2550
02:20:05,210 --> 02:20:07,250
- Slow?
- She was slow.

2551
02:20:07,690 --> 02:20:10,610
Please forgive me for being slow.

2552
02:20:10,600 --> 02:20:11,680
It's alright.

2553
02:20:11,670 --> 02:20:14,430
Is it? I see.

2554
02:20:14,420 --> 02:20:16,760
Let's go right away.

2555
02:20:16,750 --> 02:20:19,170
This errand was a success.

2556
02:20:19,160 --> 02:20:26,600
I was on so many errands today.
I came to visit Buddha and I...

2557
02:20:26,590 --> 02:20:30,630
The words burst out of her in one go.

2558
02:20:31,680 --> 02:20:37,990
Yesterday I went to the ocean.

2559
02:20:37,980 --> 02:20:41,860
Which ocean? I forgot that.

2560
02:20:41,860 --> 02:20:42,610
You forgo..

2561
02:20:42,600 --> 02:20:45,880
My father played soooo much with me.

2562
02:20:45,870 --> 02:20:46,390
I see.

2563
02:20:46,380 --> 02:20:54,530
My little brother was with me.
And mother. We were four all in all.

2564
02:20:55,400 --> 02:20:59,860
Now we all know what Sae has been doing all week.

2565
02:21:02,570 --> 02:21:04,450
I'm home.

2566
02:21:04,510 --> 02:21:06,310
Sae, did you do your best?

2567
02:21:10,240 --> 02:21:13,310
I chose pink carnations.

2568
02:21:13,300 --> 02:21:16,010
Flowers from her first errand.

2569
02:21:17,260 --> 02:21:21,000
The monk from the second errand.

2570
02:21:20,990 --> 02:21:27,670
Breaking a sweat from all the hard work and deep in prayer, her grandpa would be proud.

2571
02:21:29,960 --> 02:21:35,770
Having fought through two errands
she now fights off sleepiness.

2572
02:21:40,220 --> 02:21:44,440
This was Sae who loves giving her all.

2573
02:21:42,400 --> 02:21:45,200
She really did.

2574
02:21:50,320 --> 02:21:53,090
11 years later.

2575
02:21:53,320 --> 02:21:57,050
The place we are meeting with Sae...

2576
02:21:57,430 --> 02:22:01,860
Is this an outdoor stage? No no.

2577
02:22:01,850 --> 02:22:07,160
The girl wearing the aqua green is climbing the wall.

2578
02:22:08,110 --> 02:22:10,270
It's Sae.

2579
02:22:10,760 --> 02:22:17,150
Sae who still loves to give it her all is now in 3rd year of middle school where she's a rock climber.

2580
02:22:17,140 --> 02:22:21,560
In elementary school she came 3rd in her prefecture within the C-class.

2581
02:22:21,550 --> 02:22:24,660
In first year of middle school she became the first in B-class in the prefecture.

2582
02:22:24,650 --> 02:22:32,370
She also won a second place in another bouldering competition.

2583
02:22:31,220 --> 02:22:33,130
Amazing.

2584
02:22:32,420 --> 02:22:38,410
And this spring she became number one in her prefecture in the group of young girls.

2585
02:22:38,400 --> 02:22:41,240
A little more and she will win in the Kanto region.

2586
02:22:43,260 --> 02:22:46,510
She fell.

2587
02:22:43,260 --> 02:22:46,510
So tough.

2588
02:22:48,310 --> 02:22:55,350
She puts chalk on her hands from her bag and goes straight back to it without a break for her muscles.

2589
02:22:55,340 --> 02:22:57,680
That was all the break she got.

2590
02:22:57,670 --> 02:23:00,290
Taking the place she failed as a new challenge.

2591
02:23:00,280 --> 02:23:04,170
She grows strong from all the climbing.

2592
02:23:04,160 --> 02:23:07,990
This time she climbs only using the red stones.

2593
02:23:07,980 --> 02:23:13,860
She has accomplished it when she attaches her rope to the clip above.

2594
02:23:16,640 --> 02:23:18,380
She did it.

2595
02:23:18,410 --> 02:23:20,570
Please lower me.

2596
02:23:20,970 --> 02:23:26,810
We asked Sae about why she becomes so perfectly focused while climbing.

2597
02:23:26,800 --> 02:23:32,720
I love the feeling after I've accomplished a climb.

2598
02:23:32,710 --> 02:23:41,170
As I become able to climb more difficult ones I become so happy that I just can't stop doing it.

2599
02:23:41,160 --> 02:23:44,870
What kind of child has she become?

2600
02:23:45,240 --> 02:23:47,290
I wonder...

2601
02:23:47,280 --> 02:23:51,160
I might not have changed that much after all.

2602
02:23:53,370 --> 02:23:57,510
I still love to excel in everything.

2603
02:23:57,500 --> 02:24:01,360
And I never stopped breaking a sweat.

2604
02:24:02,280 --> 02:24:04,180
Please.

2605
02:24:04,180 --> 02:24:07,540
Always outperforms on her second try.

2606
02:24:07,530 --> 02:24:10,960
Now she only climbs on the green stones.

2607
02:24:10,950 --> 02:24:17,440
Her closest goal is to pass to the National Athletic Meet and perform well there.

2608
02:24:16,080 --> 02:24:17,440
Scary.

2609
02:24:17,430 --> 02:24:21,970
And then she hopes to do well at the Junior Olympics.

2610
02:24:22,190 --> 02:24:25,800
She also accomplished it in her second try.

2611
02:24:27,440 --> 02:24:29,570
Please lower me.

2612
02:24:29,570 --> 02:24:36,670
She does this all by herself. She has developed a splendid view of the world.

2613
02:24:36,660 --> 02:24:39,530
What does she want to be when she grows up?

2614
02:24:39,530 --> 02:24:49,110
I love science so either sports science or nutritional science. That would be a lot of fun.

2615
02:24:49,150 --> 02:24:53,400
This was Sae who is radiant from all her hard work.

